Very friendly staff.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFX57uWEVcFNszUqhFCb0RSwwtESXbGsd4v3qs&fid=0x0:0x85871f0dc12414ee"],"When":"2021-4-20"},{"Name":"Brandon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKX2INuw6e1W9fZJk-3ekgKjhPJ3r-Ql-Hsdupxyf51M_1g5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Today, December 24th we ordered our food and paid online. When we tried to pick up, they do not have our order and had to wait for another 30minutes. We always order food in this location but never again. NOT recommended to my friends and relatives.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have tried both lunch and dinner
Everything is pretty much the same.
Differences listed here from what I remember:

Lunch - only wonton soup, black bean green beans with beef, fried wonton skin, sesame battered chicken drums.

Dinner - wonton and hot and sour soupn blean bean mussels, onion rings, battered shrimp

We came on a busy day for lunch and everything was fresh except for some reason the wonton soup was so bland. When we went for dinner on a sunday night and there were only 3 other tables and the food was stagnant for a while that it developed a film on top. The wonton soup this time was good. It would be great to know before hand whether it's busy or not haha.

Typical mediocre buffet food. Lunch price is pricier is $19.95 which is ok. Food is better than uncle willys.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIJmr1xZ2_u7yglKqhx4OFDDMnKMbg_QyZMMiq&fid=0x0:0x85871f0dc12414ee"],"When":"2023-6-8"},{"Name":"Frank Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqU7w4lL0DBsy1BjK_cj8vbNltIdZkHHYfmHo3u05AoSN2BGW5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"$20 is a reasonable price for a weekend lunch. Sichuan beef is really great and you have to try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzfUfr-KkN2HIb2OC-euowUaQgKO-a-iaiKsSJ&fid=0x0:0x85871f0dc12414ee"],"When":"2024-5-4"},{"Name":"Татьяна Ковальская","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIXVxMFqXQF_UuwlQ8WsZcn2JYLhelxF3fDPghxx-eUGYGE9w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Extremely tasty food. I am happy that my friends brought me here!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWNRBMd6-ZQ6mAx8AiyCDrboeSNMqjW7DNEeOs&fid=0x0:0x85871f0dc12414ee"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Simon Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKARXZijowQGioSxiOMCg-EzyxEm1UrGAfGF9hiOguYSh8sPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The staff are nice and friendly. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Annie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAG4UtHNdn-C74S5I053c9lMdRMdh_AH35u090AgjHoFmF2GSW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our first time at Blacksheep and it happened to be prime rib night (also Father’s Day)
It was busy but we got a table right away - service was good and atmosphere was easy and casual. We will definitely be back.

Back again! Our server was awesome and the food was great! Lots of leftovers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPX3WBmq-fMVKz1JNKEt-RuLQzO9MVYYIqLj6fs&fid=0x0:0xbcea51144945bbe5"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Nathan Woods","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYlKwIGO9PHjqLgc7mRGN7qYIzJ_Yb1JOij4343pL12ye4fG4D-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Top rate neighborhood pub!

It's a little out of the way, but it has to be one of Maple Ridges best neighborhood pubs.

It's clean, well decorated, and full of friendly staff.

Today I had the wor wonton soup and a sushi cone... I wish I had ordered two sushi cones.

The soup was well worth it, full of vegetables, lots of barbecue pork, and lots of wonton!

I will definitely be back at this pub!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbVhIBTwoP2X4cqq05P6LAIhFbSeUuQtjXfPc6&fid=0x0:0xbcea51144945bbe5"],"When":"2024-8-1"},{"Name":"Queenie Chao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZJZmSpZQRAFF9t6SoJ29KP7hdKen-l5gR8pgpgRf7-1s6aED9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super friendly and helpful staff, quick service, great food (chicken parm burger), and really nicely decorated interior. Feels like an upscale pub that's had a lot of thought put into it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjV4Y_KFES66PVYVhFEqn-a3nnx0J9vDuqHi-i&fid=0x0:0xbcea51144945bbe5"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Matt L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuCHpIiV01U1r9hpBBKPXgcZIpixEgrpu-SnC2oP9naymDyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An amazing pub, lots of parking they have an overflow lot as it can be quite busy at peak times. The food is wonderful! The burgers are top notch! I also recommend the clubhouse sandwich it is also very good! Have been here many times and have never left dissapointed! The portions are a very good size and the prices are very reasonable! They also have a very good assortment and selection of fine beers and ale's on tap fresh! This Pub is worth a drive to check out great food great service and a fun atmosphere! Highly recommend the Black Sheep Pub check them out! You will leave there full and happy!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vasisht Raghavendra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJdqlfXhrv4xWlObHOUik-BEmjW2vxVvFad9PSosG433WUa8GN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The waitress who took our order had an attitude and the food was decent. But the one who gave the cheque spoke well and had a smile.

We started with chips and artichoke dip, Lettuce wraps and Chicken wings. The wings came with a small cup with lime and a liquid. The cup was actually to wipe off from eating the wings but we mistook it to be a sauce 😂. The wings are not great and we had some leftovers. For the main course we had Seafood Penne pasta. It was good and very filling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfGgVeI50HCsIw10pcAnkH2MqN_-AGqeEp_RG9&fid=0x0:0xbcea51144945bbe5"],"When":"2023-4-13"},{"Name":"Gordon Laity","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLvF4xpjTU7yoScEp9NrBctW8Wlp9ID7aWP2ruaE7h7n3FP7A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Generous portions of consistantly delicious food. Comfortable seating, Guiness and others on tap, great service,  large menu, and modern decor all contribute to make this pub a great place. The schnitzel burger, unchanged and perfectly balanced for over 3 decades, has been a great personal menu favorite.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vlad Burca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVACp8enmVuWvVrrtMIUrDg4vz6_iQ55iNBMqK6w5GqgcTHIITQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice restaurant with a pub / diner atmosphere. Food was good value. Got the clam chowder which surprised us initially for having a slightly more colorful look than the typical clam chowder you would find elsewhere - this is due to the fact that it has a bit more vegetables (carrots) most likely. It was delicious, regardless!

The chicken bacon wrap was a good choice too, being very light and tasteful. Fries were a nice addition.

Staff was super friendly and pleasant! Totally recommend this place for a brunch or evening food and drinks!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObDNCjQdNKnlVCrSNUxRyoPk5WTtyA217Iraer&fid=0x0:0xbcea51144945bbe5"],"When":"2023-9-24"},{"Name":"Brittney Yoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYmjiLDNAQSWLBLMlhCVbZAtgPXq1rS2Tob6gPAhqChDnUpMg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Definitely a no nonsense pub, great menu and large portions and even better prices. Great for sport events since there’s tvs at any point of view. Also has an amazing neighbourhood feel, the servers are so great and the Caesar was delicious (coined “best caesar in the world”, which is quite the self proclamation). Definitely will return to try more items! The beef ribs were fall off the bone sweet bbq saucy goodness 🤤","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMtSyTW1U05SDzFDByvctkri4cLXO5CUilT85vC&fid=0x0:0xbcea51144945bbe5"],"When":"2022-8-2"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Romulus Lubbong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWl63ax3o3o4tRI1t8NUxKzpyp1s6eSGkV0Q-QKsUCogPksxGiz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We tried Big Red's at the Abbotsford Airshow. Loved their Beef Chicken Poutine. In fairness, I like the texture, crisp not soggy.

HOWEVER, the sauce quantity was not enough to cover the entire box of fries, didn't reach the middle and bottom. Could you please be generous with the gravy from now on?
I would definitely try again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"chantal mishler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_a-ta-zwFaboUjK8xHMFTs-VRx5Cbdvf7S8BMeebygb0WSCA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Recently tried them at the PNE fair. It was beyond disappointing. I don't know how one can manage ruining such an easy dish, but it was honestly the worst poutine I've had. The fries were undercooked, crunchy (but not in the way you'd hope), and cold middles. The gravy was SO sad. It was the bland-est gravy I've ever had. There was no flavour. The cheese curds were good, they obviously were store bought. I am NOT one to normally complain, but if the lineup wasn't so long I 100% would have returned it. For $13+ I would have expected something atleast edible. I tossed it out after 3 bites, my friends who tried it also urged me to return it.
Wouldn't return again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Skreech xx","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXc4x6b1aP-dudAsR9a3FuhUpNF7pj7sloojuiK3LAan2FdAzY8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Got the classic poutine the other day at the luminary festival in North Delta from this truck and I was very disappointed. Gravy tasted old and It was very small for what it cost. The classic poutine was $13 and all I have to say was it was super small. Such a rip off. You could get TWO big and very filling poutines at costco for the price of what big reds costed. I 100% wouldn't recommend getting it ever again. Waste of money and time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUV69jahocJXJ5Qpy7louD-ELbmPOE6eYM1Nj6s_NTGEI-5bRlF=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Got the chicken strip poutine. The chicken strips were horrible quality and tasted bad. The gravy had 0 flavor and was not hot enough. The fries were bomb tho! EDIT- I see some are saying the chicken strip poutine is 12$?! we paid 17$!!!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeff Curnew","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJKOGpLkRh8MeITTuZ5zi75R5eK5M8fJ43s3uhiIPsXQPeX0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Unfortunately, the new recipe for the gravy is not good.  We used to travel far and wide to get Big Reds,
Now the portion was half the size and the gravy was weak and no longer authentic poutine gravy. Such a shame.  We won't return.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aaron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHacRgtrfS5scu3MsrBBl1IethxtxLJfCNuTudFilbMAs0Lw6P=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I ordered the chicken strips poutine. It came with only a few pieces of chicken. The cheese curds were cold and unmelted. Only decent part was the fries that were hot and crispy. I would not recommend this place. Overpriced and terrible quality.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emily Kasal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZ7x5LYWndAM_AD9nf6k2i-FeY_3xsTMgvio9skajGHNrhi8vV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Had their poutine at the PNE and can’t say I’ve ever been more disappointed in a poutine… it was cold and the cheese curds were just not it. Also pepper in the gravy? Really?? Yikes.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ArwadM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJgsgXFbTGDtqQIP5j1Cq6f4xf3uHjdhCwRRHQHYFzk7Z5xag=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved the chicken stripes I ordered at the PNE my friend ordered the classic poutine and he also enjoyed it. I'll definitely come back for more!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Chris Brooks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHqHQ4ilLsckCY4ImY4rfLZWbdKgeiqeu0ZNVBWabRLdK1bA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food at great prices got a 4 piece chicken strip meal half with Cajun spice half plain. Food was excellent chicken was crispy fries were crispy just the way I like it and love that it comes in a pizza box.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKqzyUZarEbKHqrcG99o8Jb-s_5iOmQ07o7uWj&fid=0x0:0x8193e4ced7d8c13e"],"When":"2024-11-5"},{"Name":"Renee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJpRD48jMFb84ki9MrfhQthafUMC2ELOrSet5Ba8_5r6ht4UA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Always tasty and fresh—definitely worth the drive! I've yet to have a bad meal here, and the staff is always friendly. I highly recommend the Cajun-seasoned fries with gravy and chicken. My only complaint is the wait time, as we often find ourselves waiting even when arriving after the scheduled pick-up time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gord Anderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIahUjBdzeJ3fJdzeREqM4ief7x1VCycxO4Dba_r9rDwRFYdw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went to Brownies today to pick up a Birthday lunch for my daughter and when I got there I was greeted by the nicest service worker I have ever met. She handled my order exactly the way I wanted and even brought it out to my truck where I was waiting. The food was hot and delicious. It made for a great birthday celebration Thanks Brownies","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxP-ADvohB6hXpEbci04qD4fdlJ8qjEvYJvIIZqjiOIuWU9BVM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Probably the thinnest most disappointing chicken sandwich I’ve ever had and I’ve been to dozens of places across the lower mainland. Decided to try this place for the first time. The menu online looks great but the experience was not what I expected.

Let me just say that the service was great but that was the only thing that gives this review a 2nd star.

The Cajun chicken sandwich was a sloppy mess and the chicken breast was paper thin. It looks thick in the photo because they positioned the breast halfway outside the bun to expose the part of it that was curled up but it was maybe half an inch thick at most. The rest it was almost non existent.

The chicken tenders were literally nothing more than dry, rubbery frozen tenders. There are far better places to get high quality freshly prepared crispy chicken.

Oh, and after eating a sandwich and 2 tenders it left a gassy, heavy feeling in my stomach so now I’m laying on my bed on a Sunday afternoon with a bottle of peptol bismol next to me.

Will not be returning. I know food costs are up but I have no desire to waste my money on establishments that raise prices while opting for cheaper ingredients. Do one or the other…. do both and customers will not keep giving you their business.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEwJFh1n2KmOXxOQkVES19TQFB4TDNNtJtHz6t&fid=0x0:0x8193e4ced7d8c13e"],"When":"2024-4-7"},{"Name":"John Wu (Bun)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfKCbONy8geXldXOzG-RUFdaf5DDFT9hZCtzgwdSb0ESQXNG4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came from Richmond. An hour drive to here. I will rate this place base by distance.

Is it worth coming to try if you aren't local? Definitely is

I got the value pack chicken and fries with coleslaw salad, also Halibut with chips

In my opinion, the chickens are worth a try. I like them very much. Base on the sign, the chickens are locally source. The flavour is very home style. I got a mix of Original and Cajun. The original flavour has a salt and pepper taste. Not something from Churches. While the texture is firm, not overly cooked. Reminds me of free range chicken. The chicken pieces are smaller than Churches.

I'm not a big fan of any French fries nor I eat alot of fish and chips. So I can comment to much on this restaurant. Won't be too fair. But, I would probably skip the fries next time. But the Halibut is not bad. Firm texture, not over cooked.

Summary: Worth a try, but probably won't specially come here again for chicken from out of town unless I'm in town for a visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0fz3IU--1aCQe5dTGakqTWHZunZzvKwPoZZzC&fid=0x0:0x8193e4ced7d8c13e"],"When":"2021-9-4"},{"Name":"Noel G.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzt56miafy6iOTVeM1GDzt7WeMhTEkWIDFideh9PNNM3c6ulXi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There was a bit of a wait, but this is understandable for  rather sought after food. There are many options to choose from. Everything so far has appeared to be of proper quality to me. The service was great. They forgot to give me a medium fries. I called back and Romy gladly offered me a large fries for the inconvenience. Hands down the best tasting fried chicken around. Well, I'd give this a tie with Popeye's Chicken. I'm not sure if this Brownies is affiliated with the Brownies from 30 years ago. I would guess so. Anyhow, I recommend you give this place a try. I am glad I have this close to home.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjzYglCTTDSuoRzPhlTUDXr51EMw6ihOD3Htvx&fid=0x0:0x8193e4ced7d8c13e"],"When":"2022-2-2"},{"Name":"Kurt Jenkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqZe4Ivp3UJYu14Rq5PV3Oy-ao_j1eXrrSdu8w0JfZOz3PU7vaCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Still the best fried chicken I've had since I was a kid. Sadly, one of only two left.
Great chicken with good portions for your money.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgXJCxrS_2ZsZgO0P8G0EoGLb9ZZpeh87YiBeB&fid=0x0:0x8193e4ced7d8c13e"],"When":"2024-4-11"},{"Name":"Mike Miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKS-ULoGM-hQ5FS0SCqc6zwNvMzL8Y7z0VdwqzjIu1CR58AtQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have mixed feelings about this place. Food quantity is pretty reasonable value for the price. That being said, it’s a bit bland and they could do better with the poutine—cheese curds are pretty easy to get nowadays instead of shredded cheese.

Wait times are always surprisingly long…even when I come twenty minutes after the estimated time, I end up waiting five or ten minutes longer to get my food.

Service is okay. Not unfriendly but pretty unremarkable otherwise.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Annie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAG4UtHNdn-C74S5I053c9lMdRMdh_AH35u090AgjHoFmF2GSW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was our first time ordering from here through Uber eats as we have been craving Chinese food.
Portions were decent, packaging was great as everything was neatly assembled and there’s also a 2-for-1 for their spring rolls and dumplings.
The food was delivered quickly and still hot.
Overall everything tasted good and we will have to try the popular entrees for next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0KDOw1bazjMeIHW9bYLWcAk6oBkGSyT-iDRLe&fid=0x0:0x55b3ae1f8ffb622f"],"When":"2023-8-13"},{"Name":"Dave backeland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVcv64Vs5yBlfxYxoVSibb1CSK_GewvZ_CHwRAGyPnm_H2NUHk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"140 dollar order no cookies and 4 soy sauce. Chow mien all stuck together and dry. Almond chicken blond but over cooked. Chop suey all broccoli no othe veg really very little chicken and beef in each. Ginger beef a bit tough but very tasty. Not worth the money. Very disappointed. First time ordering.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLqvh1y65HgADrC7fj8FbDDoU5QTvpDanEIDc&fid=0x0:0x55b3ae1f8ffb622f"],"When":"2023-12-22"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious meals! Really enjoyed the flavors of each dish and they had decent sized portions. The flavors are in my opinion "Canadianized." Which I am happy with.
Definitely will be back","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSVNWTBKlk64tJzYYpa0Pk9DkB4-cIE2xXXw-F&fid=0x0:0x55b3ae1f8ffb622f"],"When":"2023-10-11"},{"Name":"Manesh Shafiei","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVE7oGsfssj_uLcNg0FiHdMtfhxS54WeE6dbk048uYFpL0C-jZW=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered beef chow fun and shrimp chow mien.

First impression when opening the bag, 2 soya sauce packets for 2 tubs of food. No fortune cookies.

The shrimp chow mien had nice flavour and a bit oily.
The beef chow fun was bland, full of oil and soggy noodles.

Very disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwZWBKrxRmHXNZHVr-zQfZRm4N18XdLSix4dpB&fid=0x0:0x55b3ae1f8ffb622f"],"When":"2024-3-24"},{"Name":"Aaron Scott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn-lvwTGMhUxCV421M_xqu_u5MrGrT6chcjNAjFFyrJKuOzGho5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The BEST Chinese food in Maple Ridge/Pitt Meadows - Woking Dragon Maple Ridge.

Three things make them stand out: Awesome, fresh, and quality menu items that are made to order. A really cool decor and atmosphere for singles, families, or groups. And, they thing that really puts them above the rest, the people that work there from the servers to the kitchen staff to the owners, are absolutely stellar. The staff are really our kind of people. They’re always willing to connect and make the experience friendly and welcoming. Go there for dinner, you won’t be disappointed!

EDIT - DECEMBER 2023: a few friends and I eat at Woking Dragon Chop Suey House in Maple Ridge once a week. We’ve been doing it just about every week for the last 18 to 24 months.  It’s our place - we even have our regular table.

Tonight was no different. We came in and sat. The server team brought us drinks without asking because they know what we order. They don’t usually even take food orders now because we order the same things each week.

But what WAS different tonight… is that when it came time to bring us the bill… they comped our entire table. They said “Merry Christmas” and comped us more than $80 in food to say thank you for our loyalty.

This was amazing. The profit margins are worse in restaurants than almost any other business. So for them to comp us all to say thank you, we recognize just how big a deal this was.

Thanks Woking dragon and staff. You folks are amazing. We very much appreciate you.

https://fb.watch/7d4hEohP_4/","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-wn50iD6CU3_LGK68I0ozEewHbdMjFaQn1B0n&fid=0x0:0x55b3ae1f8ffb622f"],"When":"2022-4-11"},{"Name":"John Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVX_G2KhQ4UDvw4Nu1dqA3AsXfC53tIj_AZn0iIn-6oDOg1Yst1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The waiters are young people, the environment is spacious, bright, clean, and the background music is dynamic.  This is really good place!
Hot tea is authentic Chinese flavor. Noodles are not way I familiar with，but it is ok.
I took a look at some pictures posted by other people,it seems to be more delicious.
I will come back to try again!

The following is a review after a week.
I change the rating from 4 to 5. This time my family order 5 dishes, each one is authentic Chinese taste.

Finally there is an authentic Chinese restaurant in Maple Ridge!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPp-Ow7MOso06iXQ_X9iKQ98uokidx8nryL8JKJ&fid=0x0:0x55b3ae1f8ffb622f"],"When":"2019-11-30"},{"Name":"Robb Farion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7HA8fb1QGGEpC6CRgNHKUnOhvL1F-nQKaUcRfo6kSW4m_5dM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Another fantastic meal at Woking Dragon in Maple Ridge. Everything was delicious and fresh and service was friendly. We had Beef Sirloin Stir Fry in Black Pepper Sauce, Honey Garlic Pork Ribs, Sweet & Sour Chicken Balls, and House Special Lo Mein w Roasted  Almonds added. The key to having a good meal here is knowing what to order as some items are a little bland tasting - as some reviews will tell you. The black pepper sauce is really tasty and you should try anything w that! Although we did not order any this time, their spicy salted prawns are also really good. In my opinion this restaurant does all things deep fried very well. Some restaurants have doughy chicken balls but not here. My only complaint would be the portion sizes are smaller than average here but the good quality makes up for that if you order the right items.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJenNuRneIFVu8nyN4I_HGfjK-OcgrLjy4NqZB&fid=0x0:0x55b3ae1f8ffb622f"],"When":"2019-8-24"},{"Name":"Gen X Surrey Girl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnz98iwXPE1DskfLpfNg-zDV5mDy1tGmvmbNcHWdRqf6q4OTmNvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It wasn't horrible but it wasn't great either. I've been hearing so many raves about this place I had to check it out. I did not enjoy it but I went back a couple months later to give it a second chance. I thought they might have been having an off day since everyone else seems to like it. The second time it was just as bad.

(Feb 2019) My first visit I ordered chow mein, chop suey, almond chicken, sweet and sour pork for take out. The food had zero flavor. It's like they didn't use any sauce, salt, msg, soy sauce or anything at all. The noodles were cooked perfectly. But it was like they cooked them and then did absolutely nothing to them. No sauce, no spice, no flavor. Completely naked bland noodles. So the texture was great. Same with the chop suey. The veggies were fresh and cooked perfectly. They were nice and crispy. But it tasted like boiled broccoli, cauliflower, celery and mini corn. No sauce, no salt, nothing at all added. I've had worse. Some restaurants make their noodles and veggies all soggy and mushy so I appreciate the crispness. But is it common for restaurants to add nothing to these things? Or maybe they did and I just couldn't taste it at all. It just tasted like water. The almond chicken was flavorless. It literally tasted like flour and water. Again no salt or msg or whatever it is that Chinese restaurants usually add to give it that zing of flavor. The quality of meat in the sweet and sour pork was good. Cooked very well again but no flavor again. Is this an msg free restaurant, did they run out of salt, did they forget to add sauce? I've not a fan of salt, I never add it to my food and I often find Chinese food to be heavy on the salty flavor. But I found this food inedible without drowning it in soy sauce which I don't usually do with takeout.

(May 2019) Decided the give this another try, maybe they were having a bad day. Ordered the same thing for takeout plus Char Siu and ginger beef. The veggies and noodles had a bit a flavor this time but nothing special. So that's an improvement there. But the almond chicken was so undercooked. It was soggy and completely white. I'm used to almond chicken being slightly browned (almond colour). I had to pull out my deep fryer to brown and crisp the chicken for my family. The ginger beef was pretty good. I've give it 7/10. The Char Siu sounded amazing on the menu "slowly oven roasted to perfection" but tasted like a chewy, tough pork chop. We ordered enough for 4 people. Usually all the food is gone with Chinese but most of it was left over. No one in the family was really into it.

So overall good quality meat and veggies but poorly executed. You don't get very much for the price and it seems a little high priced. The staff was nice both times I went in for pick up. Very young though and inexperienced. Several of the girls looked about 15 years old. I think it's great that they are offering students in the community their first jobs. Would I recommend this place? I don't know. I know I'm never going there again because I was not impressed. But the rest of the Chinese restaurants in Maple ridge and Mission are awful with soggy mushy food and gnarly meat. So by default it makes this place "the best Chinese in town". I guess I'd say give it a try and decide for yourself. I'll leave you with this, at least it's not horrible....","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeFbAAvRIofLTWXtjgDu2doO0v-0Zf3nJALha1&fid=0x0:0x55b3ae1f8ffb622f"],"When":"2021-4-1"}]

[{"Name":"Annie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAG4UtHNdn-C74S5I053c9lMdRMdh_AH35u090AgjHoFmF2GSW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We came for Sunday brunch as it’s one of the only places that allows minors!
The breakfast special was $6! You can’t go wrong. The service was great and overall a great way to start our Sunday.

Back at the Townhall for the long weekend and a tip - don’t come at opening! It’s a bit chaotic getting everyone seated and naturally service was slower, people seated much later getting food and drinks before us 🤯
Not a deal breaker but now we know and we will be back … just not at 10am!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMw0OJNAXEZGwg3yhbufhC-2Nh0gbUOrz5_VSRD&fid=0x0:0x290c1aa19e892fad"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Max Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJOIlU5nJBhhMt4LhC3zOj5-erzOKLJv2GOSpcFK4XvUCtyZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Rating: ★★★☆
The special rate for brunch menu was very traditional and simple: sausages, bacon, eggs, toast, and coffee. However, the price was incredibly affordable. If you’re not picky about the variety, this place is a decent choice for something budget-friendly. That said, for such a simple breakfast, you could probably save more by just making it at home, especially if you’re not after the “dining-out” atmosphere.

As for Town Hall, their quality isn’t what it used to be. That said, their Thursday Karaoke Night and 50¢ Wings special are quite tempting. I might give it another shot—it’s hard to pass up deals like that. Overall, nothing too impressive, but the price and vibe are reasonable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMX1ObEQwhpfTOYg213TrKNo9zbVkalyl0OexsK&fid=0x0:0x290c1aa19e892fad"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fantastic deal for brunch in a warm, welcoming space. There's plenty of room for groups, and there are a number of tables of you're hoping to catch up with a friend or host a business meeting.

When you arrive, head upstairs to the dining room. There's an elevator and washrooms available by the bar.

Reservations are a good idea, but not required. With our reservation for 2, we were seated by a cozy fire. Perfect start to brunch.

The house special for brunch is $5.99 for 2 free run eggs, 2 pieces of bacon or sausage, toast and Yukon gold home fries. Options for toast today were white, brown or sourdough.

The food was fresh, hot and not greasy. It was seasoned well, and I didn't feel exhausted or heavy after the meal.

We also ordered Caesars ($5) and there were Mimosas available ($4).

On another visit, we ordered the Stack-O-Donuts ($12) and they were delicious. Hot and tender mini donuts covered in cinnamon sugar. They're perfect for sharing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtUGZz9klf5AP6Pb8Vfr9JbpPoBhrZ4CtIWwHF&fid=0x0:0x290c1aa19e892fad"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Lisa Simmons","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLUCbM7Sv-M1pAApVUnGKleUtAL_QtjEhlmjRjJZl7LJUXJqg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Was there on a Monday for the lunch time. Very quiet. Service was great. Nice varied menu. Good specials. Like the location because you can see the mountains from the windows. Great fireplace.

10 October 2024

Had the Chicken corn chowder and the crispy fried brussel sprouts. Hubby had the chicken wings. All great. The chowder does have some medium heat, just an FYI. Loved the sprouts.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwsp10gLTRz3ZCyazKQVsGCch_vr2YqlJpl3kL&fid=0x0:0x290c1aa19e892fad"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Sherri L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKtxbJ9ZXtI9Mw2OYEesfB51_kfb1UBrxuZDdU5-5GETSdjGw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The new Thursday wing night is really good. Able to customize on what you want added to the burgers. The burger itself was mediocre and was quite expensive for the portion that was given. $4 extra to make it a combo. Took a while to get our order of two burgers, but lots of seating to wait at. Plenty of parking as it’s located within a plaza. No dine-in customers in there during Sunday afternoon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJM9GNUwI0ru9tKcbV8xDYlbCz4S4aIqcbrnrv&fid=0x0:0x10126d01160ec565"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Payam Alavizadeh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ_ZA_YHXhgNzKTpReaxZ12Y4AWYNOtDK5ZEhHo77Gk1YUw500=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a fantastic dining experience at Fatburger! Our order included the unlimited BBQ burger with mushroom and guacamole topping and the chicken spicy burger. To start, the unlimited BBQ burger was an absolute delight. Its flavors were incredibly delicious, and the combination of mushrooms and guacamole took it to the next level. The taste was simply outstanding.

But the goodness didn't stop there. The chicken spicy burger, which came with Curly fries, was also a winner. The spiciness added a kick of flavor that I thoroughly enjoyed. The fries were crispy and perfectly seasoned, making it a delightful pairing with the burger.

What truly impressed me was the cleanliness and comfort of the dining area. It's always a pleasure to enjoy a meal in a clean and cozy environment, and Fatburger nailed it.

So, my visit to Fatburger was a culinary delight. The deliciousness of their burgers, the quality of their sides, and the inviting atmosphere make it a must-visit spot. Thank you, Fatburger, for a memorable dining experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-YLNstikJR2IRr8K1vdRkYZhv6X2jQkYgd7SK&fid=0x0:0x10126d01160ec565"],"When":"2023-9-10"},{"Name":"Clare Hamilton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjmHXghyensIvYE3dOOg7pRiT5iEI2rLXHqY3Gcojd0PnnqUY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the staff at this location always cheerful and great you with a smile. The food is made fresh and is hot good serving sizes and choices that suit everyone in our family!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Julio Olmos Lima","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJKQzzzyVzTetdPGAt4DxjDLUImVYVrWCOIEJ0E8uPrDYP3g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was fresh and delicious. Commendable customer service was given by the staff. Must visit the place, perfect for family dinner.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Payam Amiri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJnoZzz1N_QX18pt4DdBS3NmrIlTmrurlte7uFBeXVhTkdkXg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I recently visited this restaurant while traveling to Vancouver with my colleagues, and unfortunately, our experience was disappointing. The staff’s behavior, particularly the lady at the cash register, was not welcoming or professional at all. We expected better service, especially considering the restaurant's reputation. I hope the management addresses this issue to ensure a better experience for future customers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"شقایق کهورزاده","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWtWJFSRRqEzEpVa7vXF80kGxbdNCVo_XDUwe2zSFTYVSLDw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently dined at Fatburger, and I have to say it was a disappointing experience. The staff’s attitude was shockingly rude. From the moment I approached the counter, I was met with unprofessionalism and a complete lack of courtesy. They seemed uninterested in helping customers, and their tone was abrupt and unfriendly. It felt like they were doing me a favor by taking my order.

Moreover, the hygiene standards at this location were below par. The dining area was far from clean, with crumbs and spills left unattended on the tables and floors. The sight of it was off-putting, to say the least. The restroom facilities were also poorly maintained, which only added to my concerns about the overall cleanliness of the restaurant.

Good customer service and cleanliness are fundamental to any dining experience, and unfortunately, this Fatburger location fell short on both. I hope the management takes steps to address these issues to ensure a better experience for future customers","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Johnny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvkqlZ5wz-o7qQiMAPvxq4Uq26umX4_opBke6CDrVfkbGhCeuLaA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was my first time at Fat Burger, and I have to say it was a good first experience. The burger I got was so delicious with all the added ingredients. The onion rings were crispy, flavorful, and delicious. They were so good that you don't even need ketchup to dip them in. I would definitely recommend this place and am definitely going back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joanne Antoniak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTQwhPcO13h_HhVjJVUrwpHjU5MeesKhPrxV5pA1ymdZ1edFkY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Their breakfast can't be beat!!  Full breakfast at a great price ... Highly recommend!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgM_wMXqe5KQ3QYWzvm996kyQ4aROme-vmh4m1\u0026fid=0x0:0x86b3c7c731b93f56"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"Laine D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLIMPisZvLKzaOf052zpgqGmEkj-3aomQuyDEvyGDCG2jEsnw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best take out Pizza and Baked Pasta I have had in many years.  This was my first time ordering from Jim's as my neighbor recommended them to me today.  The service was above par.  The food was cooked properly, hot and flavorful.  Pizza crust was delicious \u0026 fresh and supported an ample layer of toppings \u0026 cheese.  Real Pepperoni was spicy \u0026 higher standard.  The baked pasta was cooked like I would cook it at home and the meat sauce was seasoned with just enough heat on the tongue.  Everything was Excellent.  This is now my go to in Maple Ridge for Italian Take Out food.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jackie spears","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQSpIRsoeLZKzPhRjMQrTuHhWXI2eeJUv_G6fSe8jGwzpSrvc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Jim's pizza is very very tasty. They didn't have Margarita pizza on the menu and the server who answered the phone had never had one so she is definitely going to try it after this review.  Besides the cheese both my mom and I agree this was a 4 out of 5 pizza and we would definitely reorder from Jim's again. Loved how the store put the fresh basil and Parm cheese in little containers so it wouldn't get wilted much appreciated 🙌\nThank you for letting me create my own pizza and I definitely recommend you add it to your menu 🍽️🥰💕 also make sure to get mozzarella cheese for this pizza and to have olive oil drizzled on-top for an added bonus 😃😋🤸","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8DGcCxw-ilPE-hbXd65t_ET9F2_1OxnOcyCq3\u0026fid=0x0:0x86b3c7c731b93f56"],"When":"2021-8-5"},{"Name":"Ginzo Milani (Monckey100)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZJAMXcJZ4Q-fVQ1hK4TmeQ5-UBO877OkkYfk78A4TFUsqJzc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The pizza is high quality, good drag and had stringiness to it. The cheese to tomato ratio is perfectly sitting at a 1.5:1 allowing the pizza to be gooey, Jim's has a wide variety of dips which just adds to the greatness. The cheese bread is appetizing and great, but I wish it was easier to share. The staff is very polite and really cares about the experience, waitress was friendly, this tops amongst the pizza places I've been to in Vancouver as within the top 10, it might even be top 3 but I would have to try their other pizzas. This is the small pizza and it comfortably feeds 2 people, when I return I'll probably get a larger pizza to take home and test the leftover capabilities. I'll edit this review when I do, for now if you want high end, this is definitely top tier in maple, Coquitlam, Poco and nearing cities given that there is few high quality pizza places. Jim's is unique in that it offers steak and salad as well, but that is a review for another day. Closing remarks is the appetizers for the price could be better shared, but the pizza is very competitively priced and the quality exceeds the price point, great value! Total score √ 95/100","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCO5iiv2MJytOqoOEdMfI2yyddfYUJaXApuDbM\u0026fid=0x0:0x86b3c7c731b93f56"],"When":"2021-7-13"},{"Name":"mallory haddon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJeq4qBPKlBGox9VAoFrGo0qJUo3kw75QQ9bcGFNPyoRriktA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"OMG!! Love this place. So happy with the new ownership. The quality is just excellent. Pizza is loaded with toppings. Had a family event and it was the perfect place. We had excellent service and the food was just perfect. What a great place to go with a large group or for date night. Jim's will be our go to place from now on. 100% recommend!! Best in Maple Ridge.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN31d92ZABKGlHqIwrO_92-1CTjNkhqhoBTNrlK\u0026fid=0x0:0x86b3c7c731b93f56"],"When":"2021-7-22"},{"Name":"Antonio Vidal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh_xAWsf04qNgEzZEcU9YIpjJ4mya_-AYPRaWQ1_Pj-gNwn70DRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Their chicken and fries are good. Win Win","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0XaIHY36LIo3deo49TFOYhgoDtlW_ibWkjU6P&fid=0x0:0x39acfd116e028355"],"When":"2022-6-24"},{"Name":"parsia ilbeigi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrauC9mIXpBB2Z4VuZVwA78eL8RJUbqOg2Y7QBn2dUsHwUUw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Unfortunately, this business is overcharging customers for certain items when ordered on delivery apps.

Their Texas SmokeHouse BBQ burrito, can be purchased in store for 13.99 Plus Tax, this includes the protein (steak) as well.

When you order this same burrito on door dash or Uber eats, the Texas smokehouse is listed for $15.99 and as you select it, you are prompted to add your protein as an additional add-on ($5.19 for steak) bringing the total to $21.18. This is not including delivery fee and door dash software fee or tips, those are ofcourse separate. This effectively increase the cost to consumer by 25% while this isn’t something suggested or sanctioned by the franchise head office.

I brought this discrepancy to the attention of store staff on two separate occasions though unfortunately I realized, this seems to be a “mistake” on purpose and they are unjustly over charging customers.

Hope they act with honesty and in good faith and rectify this mistake.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxP-ADvohB6hXpEbci04qD4fdlJ8qjEvYJvIIZqjiOIuWU9BVM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The veggies were nice and fresh, but even after ordering double meat, it was hard to find any chicken in my wrap…also the chicken was just precooked white rubbery strips. I hope that more locals of MR would come and taste a sample of Filipino cuisine here.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jack Pajak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7kRSq5QM1wGXm36_dbE9YR6CpcUs9VUAhu1SxvpJkrQ-nGO0N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, I was very impressed with the quality and taste of the food here. They had great oldies music playing and decor here was beautiful wood wall art. Highly recommend trying Hamada!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQ_nFRgDKiO5jihheMvnPj7ZwZQfPTTqz2tbxD&fid=0x0:0xd50fbdbb7cedb58e"],"When":"2023-10-13"},{"Name":"Kathy Mae","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKZmkc3k908cxsmCBB2K8vYHucHGQLA4nkTSCVz5EAtRUalPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The inside of this restaurant is so cute! user_reviews: [{"Name":"Stevie Rett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2nKpDs7PgS5EG7UW_ZqKWJzKAdwmF5eC7QtCaqUktoeRQYdU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I love triple Os but this location is ridiculous. I don’t know who’s responsible, the people doing the training or the employees who obviously don’t care. They can’t follow a simple instruction like “no pickles” (every time it’s an issue) but honestly the worst part is they forgot the bacon on my BACON cheese burger, on two separate occasions! It’s in the name for god sakes🙄","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kartik Salhan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJww-FQG7Bsz95pY7jcu0tOgmQd9iK30eo88vuBfQermY9Sd_e=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I used to order blueberry milkshake  regularly and the same girl used to serve me. Today i bought the blueberry milkshake and she give it to me without whipped topping and when i asked her there no whip topping she put it on later . I find out they need to make new whipped topping that why she lied to me that customer need to ask for whipped topping . You guys cab simply tell customers that you need time to make whipped topping. why you guys lie to customers.Moreover there was a guy who also like commenting on the situation going on there when i was ordering and asking about my order.Totally bad atmosphere and environment. I will not visit this store again. This happen on 7 july in evening.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ryan Rostek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQe40q7Wur_usX04S6pQo3DreBq84ohETVy1iJzLxXgMgV5g4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I used to really enjoy Triple-O's but the last 3 visits have left me consistently unimpressed. $50+ for soggy/mealy fries, squished bun, meat almost not cooked enough, no napkins, only ketchup packets... Milkshake was good so props on that (extra star).  But no response at the till to make it right. Not sure if it's worth trying again. Staff was friendly, but seemed like they couldn't help (above their pay grade)?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer Geddes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIz1j9l35iGYA-X1VDy-lA_E-guSZ_nayTsKYX4PRtkwcT2pVT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's my favourite fast food place, but is also the most expensive one in town. Milkshakes are now $8. The food here is definitely worth it though as finances permit. I pay for it by asking my family and friends for White Spot gift cards for my birthday and Christmas, and because my birthday is in June, I'm restocked every 6 months on the regular. 😁","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ajit Maski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXauawzCJKc5VNC4Q6leqYR31T4qploKeu9pbZ7l6UmQQITkisR4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you're on the hunt for some of the juiciest burgers and crispiest fries in town, look no further than Triple O's! This spot lives up to its reputation with a menu packed with delicious options that cater to all tastes. From the moment you bite into one of their signature burgers, it's clear that quality is king. The patties are always cooked to perfection—juicy and flavorful, paired with fresh, crisp lettuce, ripe tomatoes, and their iconic Triple \"O\" sauce which is absolutely to die for.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rick Cameron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLQ8Zk9P-xwSsMN8m4oOVRyZZwIvLqEoHFj3QkUJap545wTEg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Fries undercooked. Most seating is taken by lottery players. Nowhere to sit \u0026 eat.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Basil Thomas Thubel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjzZ7ZduGkrtTbUmxawUvIGvEWBIQaiKC-yREvVfpe-K2mSg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have reached triple o at 10.00 pm on November1 where closing time say 11pm, and staff say it closed, Next time try to update time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"DM Fraser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-wG-ASFdHmC1HDLf8aM2Tzzq6Co6WuDqHW-pcAvPzmjgs9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It is a normal Triple O location. Excellent food. Burgers equal to the best anywhere. Especially the Monty Mushroom Burger. I used to live in LA and ate at In-N-Out many times. Triple O is better.\nNot the fastest drive through service but still acceptable.  I have been to slower Triple-O locations.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Harsh Patel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRO8oxwi598LgL5aKg92p5xEFcdOI0MFNKNtnARfpqYYV8Sw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We've been trying each pizza place in Maple Ridge, and so far this is the absolute best pizza. The crust was very light and fluffy, the cheese was abundant, and the ingredients and spices tasted FRESH! Tasted like homemade with love. Absolutely ordering from them again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Luke Dobischok","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTQGJ4aGaK08dikO9QRHd3tGhqhCmUD7hOrs5ravrgRItIdIr2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered 2 pizzas. First one was fine with decent toppings. Not sure how the other can constitute as a "Double Hawaiian" when there's hardly anything on the pizza. If I wanted a pizza with nothing on it I would have gone to dominoes. At least it wouldn't have been $20 each. Pizza is usually good but been going downhill in the last few months. Last time both were insanely greasy on the bottoms. The dough is always quite soft which is fine, but just inconsistent results.

Been there many times. Always some huge pallet of drinks in the way of the the counter. Not sure why that can never get taken care of as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHkn7L0FGROHogr5yY4tj6_oQRHtgpxXe90nVE&fid=0x0:0xfce260b9d2a5bd2c"],"When":"2024-1-1"},{"Name":"Renaissance Man","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZfM5WhGe11WCHvIuQ-dZ-AXha1p0ur9fO16r84kZYH_g9HIpK=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious calzone and cheesy bread. Was driving through town. The guy slapped it together quick and I was on my way into gold Park. Excellent service highly recommend this pizza joint. 🍕","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfjpqV1KcHN2l8Nqkb5ca5A-28wHoCc9zS8K-N&fid=0x0:0xfce260b9d2a5bd2c"],"When":"2024-5-16"},{"Name":"Mitch C.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUigQKnsqnd6-ECKxiWLF3yOJGPZULiTcrsHXswZ-6rjxY7_wxITQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Pizza looks ok, but tasted like cheap grocery store pizza from the 90's. It was supposed to be thin crispy crust. The thin crust was neither thin nor crispy, the toppings were bland. That's not a Greek salad. The meatballs were likely from a bag. Had heard good things, but maybe that's just the taste preferences of some people. To me it was not good at all. Nothing resembles the web site photos. Even the cheese on the pizza is low quality. Never again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCjjiqh4kpjPswqVLaUP2jaP0ZpGQiJOnuJHbM&fid=0x0:0xfce260b9d2a5bd2c"],"When":"2022-4-28"},{"Name":"Cliff Shannon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLA4XmMfj0rI2QROf2AYIw_S0YIghgQOvuBZ-5fdz2FZTKZ-g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Decent pizza but terrible service. Ordered a pizza on the phone. Picked it up. Took it home, tried it. Was completely wrong pizza. Called them back and they admitted to making the wrong pizza and asked us to drive back and pick up the correct pizza. Then charged us more money for the new pizza. Never again. Will stick to the bigger chains","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jigar Rathi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWc6ll8t6niWm5-ZQ5mU4DVVvTDih5HrLrDi1SoC1I_QAqZi2XD=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best pizza ever, hands down! Best location to go whenever you want. I've been here maney times, and each time I always get hot, fresh pizza. Best customer service ever. The staff is friendly and supportive.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nadia Deol","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwU63VhDSPAx_78e1BRgOPcnmW9mOG5u55pDBF9-hhIpzgSCi4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This place lacks consistency.... depending on who is making the pizza.

I only order hot and spicy vegetarian.

If it's the older gentleman who is making my order or the young guy...I know it's going to be good.

However, like today, if it's young woman making.... guarantee that half the ingredients that are suppose to be on the pizza.... won't be. My pizza today was missing pineapple, parsley, ginger.

All the got was some cheesy dough.... definitely not the hot and spicy vegetarian.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Merle Chambers (Merle)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL432ogqcLKCtSomIeZiLDsoJEUiSMNym_sj-b2tdK79Hz_bJs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ordered for the first time yesterday.  Asked for extra sauce and extra cheese.  Did not get them but was charged. There was such a small amount of sauce. Pizza was ok but won't be ordering from them again","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Annie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAG4UtHNdn-C74S5I053c9lMdRMdh_AH35u090AgjHoFmF2GSW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Finally got to the Haney for wings night and they did not disappoint! $6.60 for a dozen and lots of flavours to choose from. We stuck with the tot-chos and wings and definitely will be back to try more from the menu.  The place was bumpin at 6:00 and our server (Michelle) was busy but amazing. Don’t forget the dog treats to go for the pup!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPW9XCqkPYo7Q2tKuRTBXyI0IMqiARmU4NKlFCO&fid=0x0:0xfb07951d10939099"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"Sina Fakhari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLV3zvlXpwBhwOvFcWOJVLP1XsIJ0Y8NWvL94iHGx9-K9fgKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Tonight, instead of going to our usual pub, we decided to try a local one near our house. I ordered mayo garlic chicken wings with blue cheese dip. To my shock and disbelief, they brought me wings that tasted like BBQ. The quality of the wings was terrible—definitely not fresh.

On top of that, they asked us to pay upfront as soon as we placed the order, which was strange and unreasonable. We had to tip without even knowing what kind of service we’d receive. I’ve never experienced being asked to pay before receiving any service.

When I asked the server to check why I got BBQ wings instead of garlic, they had the audacity to lie and tell me it was exactly what I ordered.

Overall, it was an incredibly disappointing experience. Not only did they make us pay, including the tip, before we even got our food, but they also lied to us and provided poor quality food. On top of that, when we raised our concerns, there was no response or resolution. I won’t be returning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPau853kkNIkHYxeZJr3d94-9BcLlWG69uC_Psm&fid=0x0:0xfb07951d10939099"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Shawn H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUY9e68ZGbCwagZBAeE8RIgIZ2vSkY4Utn2OccYt8ED7dTgePja=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great daily deals and terrific pub food. It might not be a Michelin star setting but is a great place for a bite and a drink. The parking situation is good, and the place is centrally located in Maple ridge. The chef makes his own sauces and they are for sale. Highly recommend picking up the Mayan BBQ sauce at your next visit. Personally I like the vibe and atmosphere of the place but it may not be to everyone's taste. If you have never been it's worth a try! Great job to chef Ryan and his team in the kitchen. Also I've been several times now and service has always been fast and friendly.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cassandra Yaseniuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbmUzj3vX3zNWXqT8wGFPZhCr7UnTkbJYnbo60aOnI2_Zz3OJA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This place is...interesting. The atmosphere isn't amazing, and it doesn't seem very clean inside. There was no drink menu, and the waitress couldn't tell us the specials or what they had on tap without having to constantly run to the bar and check.
The food was decently priced, and not bad for what it was.
Overall, wouldn't recommend it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dave J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVdGWkXv3KBdawcKYa861DrCqatGIiu-Pc4zF07bXJGsitpkI62=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I'm not a big bar or pub goer. I don't drink much. I generally go for the food. The food here was acceptable. We only had wings so it's hard to say what the rest of the menu is like.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John Wylie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxiLO8pNw0MKyOXVcjXud9cqdMnsvOkp8gFBJ0P0kvbguNlJHK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went in for the fishing  chips special with my daughter food was  great with an incredible salad was quite  . Waitress are really good definitely going back again. Maybe try the Monday night, beef dip, and pizza","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Darian Parrish","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPwIfBv41Nn_c5Hq6HdDpfX2GJtB7dWn3AVKeEhKDy1PKAs0WO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place to go watch the game or just hang out with friends. A bit of a dive but the food is pretty good, they have tons of vegetarian options, and the service is always fantastic!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Garry Hans","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7F4rQFBsl3lF9Fa4TzFDOOOWwCkB586gPVojIzbAY5K4UDg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We went last Saturday.. we were family of 8 .. when we were at entrance.. the security guy who checks id is so stupid… after checking id’s he told us to BEHAVE INSIDE… like straight up .. we were about to enter and he started giving instructions to behave inside… we went to spend birthday party that guy ruined it.. we right away decide to not to go in there .. instead we went to langley and spent like $900 in different pub happily.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Ross Farrell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK7z5kOS9KIlAAzusg7zKh4LAgseFjBjZtK4vLiqyxnUuFluQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has it all. Amazing drinks, food, and atmosphere. There's something for everyone. Board games for kids, books for adults ect..   oh the staff couldn't have been more friendly or  helpful. Definitely my favorite coffee shop!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nolan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvfeLdT7xJPAVVjy2rCnwq39qJZwxeys74Qs6poxQryb1itHGo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"When ordering coffee and food at this cafe recently, the lady taking our order became visibly annoyed with our lack of decisiveness and last second additions to our order, despite being the only ones in line. I ordered a soup, and it was served to me at an ungodly temperature. I don't think a hot holder can get soup this hot so I'm assuming it was superheated from the microwave. My tongue is still scalded the next day. Given the other reviews, it is possible we caught them on an off-day, but I can't say I enjoyed my experience or that I will be coming back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joanne Antoniak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTQwhPcO13h_HhVjJVUrwpHjU5MeesKhPrxV5pA1ymdZ1edFkY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a lovely little neighbourhood cafe.  Cozy seating indoors and outside.  Specialty/regular coffee drinks and fun snacks available.  Nice little "shop local" gift area as well.
August 5 2023 ☕
Still awesome!  Had iced vanilla lattes today 😋.  Fantastic place to sit and relax - inside or out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO7fRNTlXf-LN5bo_VjB0taC_gGGz6QVw4tRmM&fid=0x0:0x54bd5139cbba718"],"When":"2022-3-28"},{"Name":"O'Malley Katt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUswFv0nzHA7NhNwpFVResHe4Lv81x7oK88qk7321o7mi-BWKc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Recently moved into the area and this is my favourite place already. The staff are so friendly and it's great for morning coffee (including flavours of the month) or lunch, their soup it so nice and warms you up on the cooler days. There's even a book library!
Can get busy on a nice day but quality never drops!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzLDqGLBL2b-YiV01qqItPYMc0Nkrc1jygU8FY&fid=0x0:0x54bd5139cbba718"],"When":"2024-3-21"},{"Name":"Kiran Vaidya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUB6j8oAUTvPnzAEOS2ASHN4wPWHIhdEUfAL8p78-hsSYM9_9PPfA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is an absolute gem in the Albion  community! From the moment you step inside, you're greeted by a delightful array of coffee choices, cold beverages and the warmest, friendliest staff and baristas. The delicious panini, bagels, and those amazing large samosas are simply mouthwatering additions to the already fantastic coffee experience.

The community vibe is enchanting, and it's clear why this coffee shop is so popular among locals. The owner's personalized touch, knowing everyone by name, makes you feel like you're part of an extended family.

Working from this coffee shop is great experience , with ample plug points and  air conditioning to keep you comfortable all day.  For sunshine ☀ lovers they have large patio as well. And let's not forget the gorgeous library corner, a haven for book lovers.

I can't praise their coffee powder enough! The fact that you can enjoy the same excellent coffee at home is a testament to their dedication to quality.

As a small feedback, it would be great if they could offer more high-protein snacks, perhaps some more egg items for a fulfilling brunch experience.

Overall, I rate Kanaka Creek Coffee 5/5 for its superb coffee variety, friendly ambiance, and outstanding service. It's truly a hidden treasure that adds so much joy to the local community.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM26YnETFFnvm760rqWBnoG5DqHcFyGsjjCJJDz&fid=0x0:0x54bd5139cbba718"],"When":"2023-8-4"},{"Name":"Spike Luk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVljR41LewaD1cz5kVqUD3bmc9ybJSH00GIF-DrHusS8cKNejJe=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just went out for a morning ride to Maple Ridge and stopped for coffee here.  The staff were friendly.  My large vanilla latte was LARGE!  The muffin was yummy.  The patio was perfect for the nice sunny morning.  Looking forward to coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHdYFT6DuVT-AmmU34txHQsyYm0Ee-rRv34oli&fid=0x0:0x54bd5139cbba718"],"When":"2022-7-2"},{"Name":"Lisa Simmons","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLUCbM7Sv-M1pAApVUnGKleUtAL_QtjEhlmjRjJZl7LJUXJqg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great spot, lovely atmosphere.  They gladly accommodated my request for a sugar free beverage.  Hazelnut latte, so yummy. The Cinnamon buns are fabulous and huge. Met there for a book club. Was a little noisy for talking with a group. They have a big bookshelf full of books as well.  Definitely plan to return.  Awesome local spot.

Omg, the Hot Coconut milk latte, so yummy. And paired it with the cranberry lemon scone, scrumptious. Sorry, for to take pics.

Pumpkin steamer, yummy 😋","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Attila Péntek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVlXUNuyohDeoCx_oWUuRzRzImlIyN-Ho2e6eqBqYWNKnfow=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We just moved here to the neighbourhood, and have been “camping” in our new home while we wait for the truck to arrive with most of our stuff (including our coffee machine…).

Over the last few days we have already enjoyed some of the grilled paninis for breakfast and lunch, which are fully loaded, sizeable and very delicious.

Haven’t had a chance to sit in yet, but the atmosphere is great.

Glad to have this cozy corner coffee nearby!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Gerrit van Rensburg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJ4WTTgEjSQukmbjBtP62w3iBMBayoaSqVEvR0Kf729iaQfrr-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super beautiful park. Picnic tables close to running streams and under tree cover or shade and some protection from rain.
The trails and bridges are really nice with great views of the running streams and small falls.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMH8INO5c4-vggYe17HoAQl4XRvkgwiHmCSAGqx&fid=0x0:0x53c9dd48c2d2eae8"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Deependra Tomar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXc60cDz3TNdq98ZipDNo1XcS5r2ZtFYgprko8OpTL3736m-cWjNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Spanning over 400 hectares, Kanaka Creek Regional Park is a wilderness haven located along 12 kilometers of Kanaka Creek in Maple Ridge, British Columbia. Established to protect the unique ecosystems and wildlife of the area, the park provides a tranquil escape for visitors seeking outdoor recreation and nature appreciation.
The park is divided into four main sections:
* Fraser Riverfront: This section offers scenic views of the Fraser River and features accessible washrooms and picnic tables.
* Lower Reach & Fish Fence: Here, you can observe the fish fence, which plays a crucial role in monitoring and enhancing chum, coho, and pink salmon populations.
* Mid Reach & Cliff Falls: This section is a popular destination for picnics and relaxation. Cliff Falls, a spectacular canyon carved by the creek, is the centerpiece of this area.
* Upper Reach & Hatchery: Explore the interpretive center at the Bell-Irving Hatchery and learn about salmonid enhancement programs.
Kanaka Creek Regional Park offers a variety of activities for visitors to enjoy, including hiking, biking, fishing, and bird watching. The park is also home to a diverse range of plant and animal life, making it a perfect place to connect with nature.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7QR63o4deDIO1g5QLjtqYeJVEVL_itU2IkK8y&fid=0x0:0x53c9dd48c2d2eae8"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Nihit Malhotra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXfeHWYeDGkDTZNd33AgDsCmLoJ4NSwzG1vpopgAV9OU-hgspcS7Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Peaceful Park with Scenic Trails

Kanaka Creek Regional Park is a lovely spot with some good trails, perfect for a peaceful day outdoors. Parking is a bit limited, so plan accordingly. It's a great place for picnics, with plenty of spots to sit beside the flowing creek and take in the serene surroundings. The trail to the falls is only about a kilometer, but honestly, the falls themselves aren't particularly impressive—if you're coming just for the falls, it might not be worth the trip.

That said, the trail along the creek is definitely worth the walk. It has some steep inclines, so it's not stroller-friendly, but the scenery more than makes up for it. You can easily spend a few hours here, enjoying the quiet, sitting by the water, or even dipping your feet in the creek. A nice spot to relax and unwind.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCycvGpZZ9IfzCB6ge1YwWL1si4Cmrja-Q4Gov&fid=0x0:0x53c9dd48c2d2eae8"],"When":"2024-9-4"},{"Name":"Helena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiYVJyd2ntFwLRumbYS9Kznuj6jXHoPn0UkQ_zdJDM29rWiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A well-maintained Park for adventure. I was interested in the Bell Irving Hatchery. Glad to see hundreds of thousand salmon fry have been reared here. Learning more from the Kanaka Creek Watershed Stewardship Center. Great work! I’ll be back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOd2SGwK3WDk1dAdGwbnQfjoUfL3r_07R-PK-Bp&fid=0x0:0x53c9dd48c2d2eae8"],"When":"2024-6-28"},{"Name":"Chris L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlo27yi0c3tMg1MEFW8gltVROJwlBrQGtk927fnMS7KkAAA0UJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for a walk with the dog, gf and my mom here. Absolutely beautiful spot with alot of history! So many picnic tables and spots to stop and enjoy the view. The trails are well taken care of. Friendly people out there walking there dogs etc. Loads of parking. I enjoyed the bridge and the look out spots. Too cool. Looking for a good spot to check out some scenery.....this is it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNp-0rpmA_j1KKtCnctRs0htY7mhkQGUYrEJq3u&fid=0x0:0x53c9dd48c2d2eae8"],"When":"2023-5-5"},{"Name":"J. F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvnPrghjIIxyliVLQ5qdXC_aHHLxKWdRLtv7_c0XpUi4UfZmBiFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great little park with a  creak running through it!  Nice old growth Trees and shade. Has pit toilets to use the washroom and free parking. The creek is easy to explore and very pretty!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpzr-Vo-wKjvFCX4jKBDUiij-la4NWcc40Oo3x&fid=0x0:0x53c9dd48c2d2eae8"],"When":"2023-8-5"},{"Name":"Patrice Damico","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWjAfE8onCXZsWmnW9w_zvpyiMunHPXXLqQyfdyfWp-3ev2r4Im=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Loop trail beside the river is easy for almost anyone. Sometimes great things to photograph too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN--_3Yc_oy7SIAszjSafIvk043f3o-Btj3Db9Z&fid=0x0:0x53c9dd48c2d2eae8"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Tracey Huffman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBwg14S4OvEKEJxR5zxVu4-POwTW7SwmTgt1_ga7n0rOSnw72D=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I grew up in the area ,so bringing my son now that he’s grown up and the dogs to a favourite spot of mine for a walk is so amazing! We brought our dogs and they loved it too! Check it out! It’s very peaceful , and across the street is a beautiful trail we have walked along also and got some amazing photos!! Check out one of my go to places to get away and listen to the water and the birds.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFMgOQMQzLCJWUd5MVP0QwaqqNdNdTwvgzdc1Q&fid=0x0:0x53c9dd48c2d2eae8"],"When":"2022-4-18"}]
