user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Tom McDougall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0J48kC1hZM1V1aRsvHOZVDophlDmEISwqhKMFe94oVeHk06c2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beatniks Bistro - Fort Langley

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

We had an early dinner at Beatniks Bistro with my parents, and it was a delightful experience. The ambiance was cozy yet modern, making it the perfect spot to relax and enjoy a meal in the heart of Fort Langley. We were seated promptly, and the staff were attentive and friendly throughout our visit.

The menu had a great selection of dishes, and there was something for everyone. We started with the crispy calamari, which was perfectly cooked and seasoned. For mains, we had a mix of dishes, including the short rib and the salmon, both of which were cooked to perfection and beautifully presented. The flavors were balanced, and the portion sizes were just right. My parents really enjoyed the experience as well, and it was a lovely way to spend time together.

What stood out was the quality of the food and the relaxed atmosphere. The outdoor seating area looked inviting too, but we opted to sit indoors given the cooler weather. Overall, Beatniks provided a wonderful dining experience, and we look forward to returning. Highly recommend for anyone looking for a delicious meal in a charming setting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMIjf3DWc_qaY3F--653BEA8_r9sWDQKaMbjOSl&fid=0x0:0xfe43abe99f45cdb9"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Kat Sykes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUccyfg8kVkNFxM3K2eZWJ1jcQT3OuohgE_37gTeq5lt55yLpw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute little bistro with a large outdoor space.  Service was good and the food was great.  Really good burger and yam fries.  The only bad thing for
me was the amount of salt on the fries.  I don't use that much salt and had to brush off a bunch to enjoy the fries.  Street parking is limited and there is a small lot in the back for about 8 cars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjyj2vUaYdPOS6m0JaZiSkNQ7plcF3Qqq0F7_w&fid=0x0:0xfe43abe99f45cdb9"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Daniel Vasquez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfH4IGtDH-RZPfkWL0P5tVuSs9PJ8oLSHVNJs_o3NyG6_oaSvUng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It all starts with the atmosphere and location, the patio is fantastic in the summer; any occasion and for any meal, just super! The service is so good, all the staff have a smile and are so genuine in the service they provide. Now, last but not least is the food, so yummy. All the meals we tried were delicious and just perfect. Can’t wait to go back. Highly recommend it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8GDPXlpZwQiZnq1SGfjwIEjBtrW-kbGozBVmR&fid=0x0:0xfe43abe99f45cdb9"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Philip Raymond Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5EIBAgpBLsauhPMdjXym7mJ4fA8mtryDtWQIJCZfJxYXxupU8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were assisted by Kelly and she was so full of positive energy. All the staff were helpful. Busy beautiful Sunday so lots of people. We had salads, burger, fries, and drinks. Everything was fresh and spot on. The salmon was quite overcooked so it was quite dry, flavourful though. Still good.

Will definitely come back. This place is a gem on Fort Langley!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZtCzzLZ1tYW1-f2P58jLaguOuDRZ540_swUAe&fid=0x0:0xfe43abe99f45cdb9"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"WanderingNomadJunky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLV5nGXazxvMsF1gu1JToxDjQdzN7lbcZ-wJLf6VmKi487Kmt5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We got here before the rush. 9am. Brunch was 😋 delicious. The staff was very friendly. The atmosphere is interesting. Wasn't as busy as the other places. Classic breakfast 🥞🍳. Really large patio area. Prices are reasonable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPO08gSEmRYxza57UdCM-KA2jR2fiafgD3G77h0&fid=0x0:0xfe43abe99f45cdb9"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Oluwayomi Adebule","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXqcIg8ujO4XiC50cD8_FM6q8RuvnCHkeqVI4f08BodMBvibbJTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I was a bit underwhelmed with the experience. I like my food more flavorful than they had to offer. The items showing on their Google reviews are no longer on the menu which increased my disappointment with this place. It was a busy summer evening so expect to wait at least 30 minutes before your table is ready. No reservation required, just leave a name at the front desk and you’ll be given an estimated time. Busy also means the service appears slower than normal .

Fare:
Coconut prawn
Crab cakes
Short rib braised beef on parsnip puree with rosemary jus
Halibut on wild mushroom risotto

Libations:
Beatniks Shirley Temple
Virgin mule

3.5/5","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaLtkfToaxJBrzuLy5lFBgvieoGqDGJ1v4C_Bz&fid=0x0:0xfe43abe99f45cdb9"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"FAIS KHAN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlKzzS_N_VjrFHFaIWN-Z9G7c1k4XbX_BTvMFUNoBuJ0tzmcRC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have a memorable experience to share from last year at this restaurant, which led me to consider revisiting. As a local resident, I rarely explore Fort Langley, a heritage village that mainly attracts tourists. Our initial encounter with the first waitress was lovely; she was friendly, took our orders promptly, and served our drinks right away. Unfortunately, she did not inform us of her shift change. The second waitress who took over was regrettably rude and unprofessional. Despite her assurance to refill our water twice, she never returned with it. Although we ordered promptly, we waited 35 minutes without any food. When we finally flagged down the waitress, she explained that there had been a mix-up as she assumed we had finished our meal. When our food finally arrived, it was a mixed experience. My wife's gnocchi was good, but my fish and chips were disappointing; the fish was undercooked and frozen, making it impossible to cut. The manager, who was very positive and kind, offered to replace my meal for free. I declined, considering the subpar service we had encountered.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6tkrcqkdnNfWUf01lAEQT9DVTO6JJ8PVX4kmB&fid=0x0:0xfe43abe99f45cdb9"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"Spike Luk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVljR41LewaD1cz5kVqUD3bmc9ybJSH00GIF-DrHusS8cKNejJe=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was a warm Saturday afternoon so we decided to get some shade under an umbrella at Beatniks Bistro.
We were greeted by a friendly hostess who was also responsible for clearing and cleaning the patio tables.  My wife and I were thinking since it was fairly busy the restaurant should have had someone host and someone else clean and set the tables.  Fortunately, the wait wasn’t too bad.

Once we were seated we ordered our drinks.  Somehow my wife was given a virgin Peaches cocktail instead of a regular Peaches cocktail.  I was wondering why my wife was not turning red.  Later the bill showed me a nonalcoholic drink was entered.  It tasted yummy though.
My IPA was cold and refreshing.

The deep fried pickles were good.  It had a nicely seasoned crispy batter.  The dipping sauce was just ok.  Personally a dill sauce would have been better.

The Artisan salad was fresh and crisp.  The amount of dressing perfect.

The salmon burger was good and came with nicely seasoned fries.

Overall it was a good dining experience and we would dine there again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7UT8AOPYwRxdwCdsDZmRvHv55kTZyEaHmJeAU&fid=0x0:0xfe43abe99f45cdb9"],"When":"2024-7-1"}]

[{"Name":"Mellie Fricker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXedPrBha6Dr5UkAzDR8QJg67GQLCT6B8dgmXQ74_XOEoPfcF8i=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I came to Rail & River last night for our anniversary and really enjoyed ourselves! Our server was very friendly and the food was fantastic!

We started with the crab dip, which was very yummy and had the perfect dip to chip ratio, which is hard to achieve! Definitely recommend. For our mains, my husband had the steak frites and I had the crispy chicken sandwich. Both were delicious. The chicken sandwich was one of the better ones I've had!

We will be back! 🫶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipND73hA99uhQmr-f0gSRmDHbzWP4xVvk6cVWBck&fid=0x0:0x4dd0c7124faa2796"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Spike Luk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVljR41LewaD1cz5kVqUD3bmc9ybJSH00GIF-DrHusS8cKNejJe=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It’s the BC Day weekend and we decided to visit Fort Langley.  After a short walk we decided to dine at the Rail and River Bistro. The server was great.   Dog bowls were at every table.   We ordered an IPA and  Sangria.    Both were yummy.   The lettuce wraps were super flavorful!  My beet salad presented beautifully and tasted fresh.   The Brie burger was juicy!  Overall it was a very good dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJwFZIhdo1oQvTXIG7txCas9XpglhmcwXRi_rw&fid=0x0:0x4dd0c7124faa2796"],"When":"2023-8-7"},{"Name":"Volodymyr IV","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZVGyvm5axHp2o0FXy9Qi9k5Kf-vIAC9ZH_P6Y5QSR5XqiYTr_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was a great time to meet my friends, I fall in love their chicken Karri soup 😉 A waitress was kind and polite! [{"Name":"Foodie Vancouver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6n06QAfqStqer1ZgBILsv-fiSHmrGRZuznSS1ny9iQFfb_Ognuw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a cozy, 24-hour spot that’s perfect for comfort food cravings at any hour. They offer an impressive variety of poutines and milkshakes, so there’s always something interesting to try. The chicken wings are flavorful, though a bit on the sweet side for my taste. The staff are warm and welcoming, adding to the inviting atmosphere. It’s a great place to relax and enjoy some classic comfort food options whenever you need a bite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9kc8lZVdGuadhPWC3Yx1Mof-WY6UkjxVzXTuz&fid=0x0:0x7685afc730c4d19e"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Retro vibes, great service and hot food. Rocko's 24 Hour Diner a great spot to visit, especially if you're traveling further east along Highway 7.

We visited early in the morning, while traveling to Hope. Breakfast was exactly what you'd hope: warm, quick, and satisfying. The portions were great and it's a fun space to let your eyes wander while waiting for your food.

I wouldn't mind popping in for some coffee and pie on another drive through the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxdFF-ZhQ9OtscpvlnXJWNW6FpX4_ZcPjucWMm&fid=0x0:0x7685afc730c4d19e"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Armin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVKfPvn-jqW8hTOlU1VeElw6vFvjre9PTWSba_96soEJn4hAFVjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a fun 50's Dinner famous for being in tv shows. Definitely try their milkshakes strawberry or vanilla is really good! They have soo many food options. The poutines are over all great and burgers are just okay. It's would be great date spot if you're willing to drive an hour from Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSO3KFvLlA1QDcDFne2UuQU5exuPlSYWX1jQPz&fid=0x0:0x7685afc730c4d19e"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Josh Howes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1JvDnFH-zR0ZYgOqbaDNkGdRCNfAiWaGE_D_VHBr1CtKBLhMM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Drove 2 hours from Vancouver to try Rocko’s, and I’d do it again in a heartbeat. Heard about this place through Riverdale. Food came out super quick and was delicious! Vibes were IMMACULATE in there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOar1iOdaGG4Y22UBjacb2XrdUYlDftMg-jr2Bl&fid=0x0:0x7685afc730c4d19e"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Sunny Suwanichskul","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWz2PYCAbXMo8xRGVddgQHeJYZJB52HAGmtV8q4BFVMUoz1uWTdhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was decent, milkshakes are really good. Always fun to come here with friends, love the vibe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnymLOo_nxbLQ5Dwh-wQFcF_iKZKxdSI1Kf600&fid=0x0:0x7685afc730c4d19e"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"James Mendonca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDOYVs1G-8iT9QF6Fj3_nUauDo1DS6zISrEp3lZ9wij4inDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I have been to Rocko's Diner a few times and this restaurant is pretty good as far as variety goes Some of the food is worth trying while others are mediocre. I have recently come back there to have the Deep Fried French Toast, which I found to be exceptionally good. The French toast tasted very deep fried yet crunchy and warm as well. It also comes with strawberry sauce and butter syrup for more sweetness.

The best thing to have there are the milkshakes, which they come in a variety of flavours. You can even have two flavours in the milkshake if you want. When I asked if they could make an Eggnog Milkshake, they were courteous enough to go through the trouble.

The interior look of the establishment looks nice with their 50s theme they have going.

Overall, Rocko's Diner is a decent restaurant with some creative entrees to offer and would not mind coming back there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhfXmvacwQRLglkvW6jKEPGT6LsGKhZbJkcc0a&fid=0x0:0x7685afc730c4d19e"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"param parkash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4GjTwUYwzDq_M1KDsLxtYNUaLlLQSsnVHDF3ZC-Xyz-4wozxNZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The drive to this place from Vancouver is fun and the food is also good. Don’t forget to try their milkshakes. Portions are big and price is adequate.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPo7rpavDCA-2DZGUfvSC-1NXgBr2c4g_Izad6d&fid=0x0:0x7685afc730c4d19e"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Shanky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6MgBgm1IStUylztVIPiG7x5geyv4SwBLPV3O9LHQFrfnpPMye=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food was mediocre, to be honest. The milkshakes were alright, but nothing special.

However, the service deserves a 0/10. I don’t understand how they can enforce such a double standard. They have signs that say “abusive behavior is not tolerated,” yet their servers are apparently allowed to mistreat customers without consequence.

I usually don’t complain, but one server, who appeared to be of Asian descent, treated us quite poorly. After I asked a simple question, she responded with something like, “I hear what you said; you’ve already said it too many times.” Her tone was dismissive and rude.

I’m not someone who expects perfection, but basic respect should be a given in any service interaction. This experience has left me with a bad impression of the restaurant, and I don’t think I’ll be coming back anytime soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFQD8d9EN0xtLjqZzVAP8O26bsucP0YmBMZPht&fid=0x0:0x7685afc730c4d19e"],"When":"2024-9-22"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Eva Zia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJp1CScTOq-jdIBVBA-K4f_r74TZU-kRd9MclConVIiSCPfy3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Oh, I can’t even begin to say how amazing this farm was! It was so enjoyable. There was no entrance fee, and they had both a strawberry and a pumpkin patch. The store was so big and beautiful, with fresh products, and the bakery offered all kinds of pies like pumpkin, apple, and peach. The fall flavors and the coffee were just perfect. The winery was really unique, with a fireplace and chairs shaped like horse saddles. We went on the day of the giant pumpkin weigh-in competition. Everything was fun and interesting, with lots of space for photography. The staff were polite and kind, and there was free parking. You definitely have to visit this place—you’ll love it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9yJFmrjnaDRbqW7q-QjaB631pRET1dGCBaHmb&fid=0x0:0xfe96a7a5520a4232"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"wah chi yip","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKKBykHMUbkrtJ4cwRRXsjOnAzAcOzwrpq-XVjovUt6A3trFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a great farm all year round. You will find many good stuff and have fun there.  All we know they have good berries for u-pick in summer.
We enjoy the fall season since we still have good waffles and so relaxing in the park setting sitting area.
I do love their corn pizzas and baked goods in summer but it's too hot for us lining up for the good food.
Summer is great for younger family enjoying the u-pick and the food patio.
The pumpkin season and pumpkin patch are nice too.  There are lots of fall supplies and gift items in the Market. You can grab some pies and ice-cream for the Thanksgiving.
The Giant Pumpkin Weigh Off is an interesting event you should not miss.  Plan your visit next year since it was happened just 2 days ago.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdBZ7yO2heVBvHrkpc4YAU3SmB_ZzOM9KHANUw&fid=0x0:0xfe96a7a5520a4232"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Rolando_ Rose","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIQBfjayv2V3eqQ6nmwU1uOEqgsWCG5VdwRxO3uXCF1EsXQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What an awesome experience during Canada Day! Fun-filled throughout the day with all the activities, live music performances, wine tasting, strawberry picking, market/bakery and of course waffle bar with the best whipped cream I have ever had. Great location with parking lot. Highly recommended !!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXwD1KI99No500IThPueYXFERCBtVB0SuEfrg&fid=0x0:0xfe96a7a5520a4232"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Asha Talbert","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9jksFqYLuaGUu05pgj-b8XCSY-_nIpjxC_AoFHw8FZ54_9EYREA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the most beautiful and entertaining spots to visit in Langley. There was so much to see & do. I was impressed that they went all out with the Fall season decor.

I tried their famous waffles which were absolutely scrumptious (especially the Strawberry one). Their shop is full of a lot good quality merch and assorted food flavours not easily found elsewhere (and reasonably priced too).

The best part was the wine tasting with Stephanie. She was so much fun and highly knowledgeable. It was truly a memorable experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgyNPIk_4siTXaKI_aK_mTzgDhusqgVVodDsuI&fid=0x0:0xfe96a7a5520a4232"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Steven Wen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLIIHw2cuDv4B_TN137fu9G3ROrZvNmMTnR_BOEt-DfieCOEw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great time here at the farm.  Had smoothies and waffles. Picked our own blueberries.  That was a lot of fun.  You but a basket (different sizes available) and then board a shuttle bus to their fields. These blueberries were really amazing. The kids had a competition to pick the largest blueberries!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlDkqICL7bTL0yBE6-Yg1IyUB_q2ECGhtE32z5&fid=0x0:0xfe96a7a5520a4232"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Fred Olores","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLrGp57nrelWQQC3KQ16bE72aNj7OcktyyhrMnxMfU6XWvxbzQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Krause Berry Farms’ strawberries, and blueberries are the best! The strawberries we picked were really fresh, and sweet.

Their waffles are delicious. It is worth waiting in line for! Going early (especially on a weekend) is recommended as the lines could get long. There’s plenty of seating available.

I have yet to try their pies, cakes, and wine. They all looked so delectable from the shelves.

Their gift shop also offers cute trinkets.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQiXTuTC33nO8JmcYCnQ1_P1vgF80ZBPqugZPS&fid=0x0:0xfe96a7a5520a4232"],"When":"2024-9-11"},{"Name":"Leah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKarmcGZ1Js35SCZKS4LzTbiBHhnd6ukNdOqfbApRvwTocr3k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve visited Krause Farms for several years, apologies for the long review!

Krause is great all year round, they have activities for all ages, like outdoor games, a play area for kids, u-pick, gift shop, wine tasting, and waffles on an inviting porch overlooking the fields.

Service is top-notch! Happy smiling staff who are helpful and knowledgeable.

•The Shop 5/5: endless items - pottery, berry infused coffee and tea, pickled veggies, jams, syrups. The handmade Blueberry Honey soap is my favorite.

•The Bakery 4.75/5: scrumptious treats and baked goods.
-Pie In A Jar 5/5: loaded with fresh fruit, strawberry glaze, custard that’s not too sweet, crust that’s not too heavy, must try!
-Cinnamon Buns 4/5: I’m not normally a cinnamon bun fan, but theirs changed me; however, the last two times I’ve had them they’ve been on the dry side.
-Shortcakes 4/5: light dough and sugar, loaded with seasonal fruit. My favorite was Apple Shortcake in 2023.
-Popcorn 5/5: Caramel Corn.
-Baked Pies 3.5/5: nothing against their pies, but when at Krause, I prefer a unique treat.
-Waffle Bar 4/5: light, fluffy, heaping with fresh fruit, syrup, and whipped cream (Blueberry’s #1). My vegan friends gave vegan/GF waffles 4/5.

•The Porch 2/5: great service, but not quick service. Went on a Monday at 2:30pm, no line, one slice of pizza + fries took over 15mins. Two weeks later, it was a busy day, took 20+mins for my friend to get a slice of pizza. Bottom line, prepare for a long wait.
-Roasted Corn Pizza 3/5: $8.50 per slice is steep, but portions were generous. Loaded with corn, cheese, a little artichoke. Crust was tough, but I think it’s gluten-free, which is a texture I’m not used to.
-Farm Fries 5/5: piping hot, shareable with 3-4 people (two of us ate half). I wish they sold half-sizes.
-Blueberry Milkshake 1/5: in Krause’s defense, I should’ve taken it back, I’d like to think they would’ve made it right; however, I had to get home and didn’t sip it until I drove away. For $9, I expected greatness, what I got was a liquidy mildly flavored blueberry milk. It wasn’t cold or thick like any shake I’ve had, and overpriced for the size. The shake took over 10mins. The Porch issues are unlike anything I’ve experienced at Krause, hopefully it improves.

Krause Farm is fun for many reasons, do yourself a favor and check it out!

P.S. in the off season, be careful of potholes!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCKqMhQFVsM5nLO-2waK1vD8tZ0Yr85rA1lDUm&fid=0x0:0xfe96a7a5520a4232"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Ramin Mohammaddoust","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDCbSRb6vq4cTA5D-g_tlXR8PAr89iMl3ZB2Z6TYcmHQ44kw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A pristine and beautiful location, the perfect place to relax during the week! It gets quite crowded on weekends. This picturesque venue offers a serene atmosphere, ideal for unwinding and recharging. The well-maintained grounds and enforced rules ensure cleanliness and hygiene. While weekdays provide a tranquil experience, weekends tend to be bustling with visitors. Overall, it's an excellent spot to enjoy some peace and relaxation, especially if you can visit midweek","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcVsdlCZamE930AYqhD5qT0_J5icj4kkhH8cRi&fid=0x0:0xfe96a7a5520a4232"],"When":"2024-8-14"}]

[{"Name":"David Tomlinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWeebA1PMrrmuv4hPWhfRC7T3fZP_mmx-afa-rPxvLvt7LN7g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down, one of my favourite cafes for years now. The thing I love about this place is the fresh food, all made on site throughout the day, and all made with simple locally sourced ingredients (a story the owners really need to tell). Personal favourites include the rhubarb cream cheese danish, the breakfast croissant (or burrito) and the amazing chocolate chip cookies (with just a taste of salt on each one). During the summer months the evening wine bar is one of Fort Langley's best kept secrets.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmLmjeHM_fmky64NWFFjy8MivHrmcPWeewyT8&fid=0x0:0x8e0cf664852e7f53"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"wah chi yip","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKKBykHMUbkrtJ4cwRRXsjOnAzAcOzwrpq-XVjovUt6A3trFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a hidden gem in this small town.  The tea, coffee, baked goods are all great.
The staff are friendly and helpful.
When we visit this time, may be they are really short of staff.  It takes more than 30 minutes to get the drinks and baked goods.
The courtyard is so pretty with some good seating old fashioned chairs.
A nice place for a tea.  Hopefully, the line up will be shorter next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNreasOQwkfHh_lvL6wENePhwzchN5rns8HWoBo&fid=0x0:0x8e0cf664852e7f53"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Elisa Kazan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfnXq79FXK6SM_3Qr0x9E7eqGAf2iM5e785pouauMfz2nICrvAIg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"A cute cafe with indoor and outdoor seating, lots of baked goods, kombucha and alcoholic beverages. A little too bitter my liking and no seasonal drinks but the cute atmosphere made up for it. I noticed a lot of gluten free and even vegan options for baked goods.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUUMaRR7OIT4ui10e1mnR16A9KIeDdQCrCCtk0&fid=0x0:0x8e0cf664852e7f53"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKy_RY7OyFpWDMGpBPfEcNdhNvd_Bt7gU5qWs4wH5XumgCFAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place is such a little gem in Fort Langley. Their matcha latte was perfection…
I hate to say this but their cappuccino was the worst I’ve ever had. Barely any coffee aromatics and it wasn’t cheap. I will definitely be coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOvNnv_XdRIGRoxSada8c0JPMKsR9NPtj28rmY\u0026fid=0x0:0x18f5842cfa1ed07c"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Bradley Gionet","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSEZxT9bss5Wm-8sYZqNZvpWBvD6hTQuaiH051enZwW5r2mA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I have been to The Fort many times and have often acclaimed them to have the best Fish and Chips. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Eunice Zhao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_m19zpDnShMlACSrl6S-cDalRdCNjiwxQ6t6OmcK7Ajk5cQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you're passing through Mission, I highly recommend this nostalgic restaurant! The ambiance is absolutely beautiful, and for just $8, you can enjoy a delicious soup served with freshly baked focaccia. There's also an open-flame pizza oven and brewing equipment on-site, making for a unique and memorable experience. The beer selection is especially interesting!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUlqe186HdfDIc3ZO58A19rbaAzY7-h3br5BQ&fid=0x0:0x13b13c19a762a2f4"],"When":"2024-12-25"},{"Name":"Esther B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGfFac41uM2155zyohXZEp3tg0WziSeOZFXPgc0hnTU6GP5ecm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was not amazing. The pizza was too much crust and not enough topping. It was also on the greasy side and very salty. Not awful but nothing to get excited about. Their in house brewed root beer was excellent though.

Service was amazing. The waitress was super friendly and quick.

The atmosphere was rustic and laid back. We were in the family section and it was surprisingly quiet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOIYn7MyhI9wBzYpTJMCF0hHonfx0Lymn_lvUV&fid=0x0:0x13b13c19a762a2f4"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Val Phelps","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVt16bYFSmCYJrTtFnISGfVeuD0t6mGHLjEOBZjyodkTlcx-9xh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Rustic atmosphere, many separate seating areas.  Very friendly server who was attentive. However the food was a disappointment.   We had the pot pies which were the special of the day.  I had beef.  It was topped with mashed potato and gravy. The mashed potato went right through the pie, not just on top.  I  found just 2 small pieces of beef , and 3 kernals of corn.  Mainly pastry and gravy.  My husband's chicken pot pie was similar.. hardly any chicken.   The fries were warm and not hot.  Tea was lukewarm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPw6Ratapha6Zqh_19lOO3aFV63A9J3KKqA-bX&fid=0x0:0x13b13c19a762a2f4"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"WILLIAM REN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKRmqUVmhhErGGqKi-Bzn0et1-EnBX9lgvZO2NQ0f1pzZpZEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best restaurants in Mission. When you drive on Lougheed Hwy through Mission, this is the restaurant that you should step in. Perfect atmosphere, delicious foods, amazing beer and nice service. So many collectibles, antiques, and memorabilia relaxing your busy minds.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEgYHelXPFKZF-1JfWY-AU_MbT1w-jQaUGrdxw&fid=0x0:0x13b13c19a762a2f4"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Djambe Jenkinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLAILxxqgEid-EtV0BMy_CwzD-_DthvwsqK-N6mIVtxjihQqpv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went with a group of 4 in early afternoon got our food fairly quickly after ordering.

The "Garden Lovers Pizza" is SO good. A different taste than the usual veggie Pizza with garlic aioli base topped with such veggies as diced yam along with the carmalized onions.

$24, I could only eat 2 slices so we got dinner now!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkPIm2Qa81hKyrQdjDGEPz2MjBbrhKRGFp10kp&fid=0x0:0x13b13c19a762a2f4"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Joao Vitor Squillace Teixeira","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVre2HU9USWnH_BKgIvlf5ntQPo2UXFQuDjZmUbEblonP1d8PcUBQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best and fastest services I ever gotten in years! Price is pretty good too. Food is not too bad","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdmoHj0td2ouiI4wYzs8719QK0_QC88DMAQIQ7&fid=0x0:0x13b13c19a762a2f4"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Rob Douglas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrE7Zzu9fTeFqKw5ZmTcq-C0pbrApWETpudRgSfvIMafBu7HFzrg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food and drinks are great, lots on draught including in house brewed beer. Fish and chips are excellent. Highly recommended.

Large patio with smoking and non smoking areas.

Cool atmosphere with log building and many antiques as decoration.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvamaBgjtADHKLXOXKVcHj9Or-VSQPByvOKpkU&fid=0x0:0x13b13c19a762a2f4"],"When":"2024-5-10"},{"Name":"Jo-Ann Ashly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvnqw4eEdy_Mt93CIpH6Uqm9KdVpnj-5tWLisjmmPd_C-nI5hX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our staff went here for Christmas dinner event. Practically everything we ordered was phenomenal and delicious! (One person didn't love their pizza, too many raw onions)

I ordered the spicy crispy chicken salad. It was a huge portion and very delicious.
The twisty pesto breadsticks are also really great! I'd get those again.

Two people had the chicken fajitas and they were massive platters. My colleague had the Christmas burger and it looked so amazing that I'm going to go back just for that.

Our servers were lovely, polite and very quick to attend to us and get us drinks and such.

I hadn't been here in years because of previous bad food but I am now going back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNnd3GOKPvd--avmLkJCND3c5BTs6bzTAY4bas2&fid=0x0:0x13b13c19a762a2f4"],"When":"2023-12-20"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Mochi Yamaha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKxEvadgO4wrQJ-lDz7F3fW-muiNbHvLJLXV__5XsEDvWEZwA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice restaurant with decent food and great customer service. Casey and her fellow waitress efficiently and effectively handled a large party of over 40 hungry athletes and parents for dinner. Ordered the chicken and waffles and food arrived in a reasonable time frame. Everything went very smoothly. Great job!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipME5tKQsRwGfx2RdV1UKUIOdjNS0u9JibkNuleZ&fid=0x0:0x71380e83264b3d4d"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"James Mendonca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDOYVs1G-8iT9QF6Fj3_nUauDo1DS6zISrEp3lZ9wij4inDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came to this restaurant before when it was called Rockwells and I did not like the food or the service back then. Now known as Five Forks, I came for dinner and had an excellent experience eating there. The waitress was very nice and showed great gaiety in serving me. I order the Lobster Mac & Cheese, which was their chef's special and their Blue Hawaiian cocktail. The Blue Hawaiian was very good and can taste the Malibu Rum and Blue Curacao in it. The mac and cheese exceeded my taste buds in how good it was. The entree has a nice gooey consistence from the cheese was baked, while the alfredo sauce was so flavoursome, and they make the sauce from scratch too. Despite the name, you are given one lobster tail for the mac and cheese, however the lobster was still great, especially when it is paired with the macaroni and cheese. It came with garlic toast too that I enjoyed. When I came there again, I ordered from their Brunch menu. I ordered their Forks Breakfast Bowl with coffee. Then entree tasted great overall; the rice tasted excellent, especially when paired with the hollandaise and salsa sauces. The coffee was good, not the best though. The interior design of the restaurant looks very high-class and clean as well. Because this is a large restaurant, there are different sections for you to dine at and the waiter would ask where you like to sit at. But I still recommend anyone to come and eat there during anytime of the day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJGhsUhQgTW7DbxupBbeswsoWrPddWCQliqPGr&fid=0x0:0x71380e83264b3d4d"],"When":"2024-8-11"},{"Name":"Rayanne Boehm","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7nXtx0vS86bw2PHY_udvCXyxr6MAucicGyxiWuXoTRwurJXG0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The husband and I enjoyed our time here. It wasn't too busy, but the food was delicious.
We got a starter of nachos with a whiskey smash, blue Hawaiian and bartenders special drinks
Then the main dishes are fish & chips and a 6oz sirloin steak.
And of course I had to try the cheesecake to celebrate my birthday, overall we had a good night.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJnObjhShKigKdfr4eV3eNxp0JDf0Pw0NLvViV&fid=0x0:0x71380e83264b3d4d"],"When":"2024-4-19"},{"Name":"Paulina K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHESGuv2e44yh_7pNCkjXfHsSmzMLHqmPnws63OHRE0hDZGw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"They have an amazing view - the food came pretty quick but was fairly simple & bland. Quite on the pricier side, but the decor inside the restaurant is 5 stars for sure. Service is excellent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6B_WySm1bJo-Wd6oWfLNreQejExYeeUyUK87M&fid=0x0:0x71380e83264b3d4d"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Sarah Cheltenham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJzzdBsJXPMc-ChlsRzPojcMwPD7SwWrk5K5Ohbo8KvfXYtYg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We did take out supper for the family tonight, what a mistake.  Our butter chicken came without the bread so basically we paid $26.00 for a cup rice and 6 pieces of chicken in a mediocre sauce.  I had the spaghetti which tasted like it was from a tin,  my meal was also missing the garlic bread.   The kids had the chicken strips which were tiny but had a ton of fries.  I wouldn’t return or recommend this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPI1f-N8s1UQ17W2xhHbQLPK3KMRjXX6ghyR5SF&fid=0x0:0x71380e83264b3d4d"],"When":"2024-8-28"},{"Name":"CM C MAC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9vmUDmNdEn-qNdF7VbuscNFEwru-AsEdenMbN2Qoc0g4p_vUXog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An excellent vibe when we first walked in. We ordered soup of the day, cauliflower bites, fish tacos and beer battered fish and chips.
The cauliflower was outstanding! However, the fish was bland on both meals but Fries were excellent.
The soup came out way too hot and took quite a while to cool to edibility.
I brought my concerns to the server and she did an excellent job in speaking with her manager asap.
The manager came to our table and handled the concerns professionally and courteosly. Very impressed that our concerns were immediately addressed.
We will definitely be back when passing this way again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sean Heidstra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKw8HLsqCObzrWAHFP5JvJYF3woSmCrLLoedHFINDFqhEIf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was a Monday, very slow ( I was a hotel guest). Whiskey was cold, steak was blue rare, and the cheesecake delicious. Server was great, would recommend. PS: don't let the hotel-that's-showing-its-age that's connected taint your image of the place; its clean and classy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Donna S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIL8dps5XjEG60llDeFgPQhj7Hzw_5Zn8BZma3ppiIXa7b6O5xtQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Finally got in to check this place out. I've always loved the atmosphere of this spot. It wasn't busy at all. Food came out fast. Ordered the cheese burger for the kids, myhusband had the smash burger with onion rings and I had the buttermilk salmon Hoagie with house salad I believe it was called firecracker sandwich or something along those lines. There was a buttermilk chicken option that would have tasted better with the sauce and toppings. All in all it was good. The kids menu was 14.95 and doesn't include a drink or dessert/ice cream. The burger was a good size but after a drink its $18. Most kids menus have that included and I think it would be a smart move. Their burger buns were ok but I'd love to drop a pack of my homemade buns off for them to give a try 🤣. This place has a lot of potential. I would love to give them a list of my ideas to help their business. Lol waitress was nice. I hope this place does well. Prices a bit high but thats just becoming the new norm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1mIhGTHmc1H7NBPzwRqjqwdco5RGHCBmF8tNR&fid=0x0:0x71380e83264b3d4d"],"When":"2023-8-12"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Jordan Blaker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_iD6bb17qljNA2aSFr9JfMC0Jg6j51TZ3bv9L9X_-KFOAVyjatg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Such a nice and quiet Italian restaurant. The food is delicious, and the staff are very friendly. I have come here multiple times and had great experiences every time. A great place to go with friends or on a date. The location is good, and you can wonder Fort Langley before or after your meal which is nice. The restaurant is hidden beside Wendell’s so I don’t know if a lot of people know it’s there, so I’ve never had a problem getting a reservation. What I also like about this restaurant is they accommodate bigger groups, even though their restaurant is small. We had a family dinner with about 10 people and they did a wonderful job taking care of all of us.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwMM7LSaT5OlSCHdD52o6Z3RPqxXH6GZ2bDBvh\u0026fid=0x0:0xf80280c4edf81822"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Eva Zia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJp1CScTOq-jdIBVBA-K4f_r74TZU-kRd9MclConVIiSCPfy3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We chose this place for lunch with our friends, I wish we didn't choose it. The quality of the food is poor, the service is awful, the men who took our order behaved very rudely with disrespect, he didn't take our order politely, he didn't take the bill politely, his behaviour with, racism completely made us feel bad, the amount of food is very small and the taste is ordinary, and it is also expensive compared to the amount. It is not recommended at all Even if you are hungry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxUpSTRrgtSNr-BJlLo5ebE39rlx3qIMYwNXxY\u0026fid=0x0:0xf80280c4edf81822"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"Suman Kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWA9Ue8ieMt0LJ2dBJ1w71cVbjmtHwxELi3E5si5x1Cseu1w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was the best place to celebrate our daughter's Birthday today. With great food and the exact ambience we needed, it was also embellished with a Birthday wish, song and even a dance by the dinner singer. I'd like to thank him and all the rest of the diners who joined the celebration, and for that moment we felt that the place was filled with friends. Very grateful to everyone who made it special for our girl. Appreciate the great service, food and the hospitality of the ever smiling young ladies. Will keep visiting always!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marnie Eudela-Umlas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXg_gVRD_Hd9V3XIUh6_P71KHCryea9xsHYGqrZHTuXW_jdxEU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our first time here and it did not disappoint. We ordered Lamb Shank, Pizzas, Pastas, Calamari and Desserts and they were all good. Price was okay and service was awesome too. I liked the Patio dine in which was perfect for summer. We will surely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcMisBVJezJpJcvHJk-qRGkcMXBoSPtXN3NqnO\u0026fid=0x0:0xf80280c4edf81822"],"When":"2023-8-20"},{"Name":"Taz C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ235c-1POJF85QGI4N_CFSzUmrADwRBXdKObCvBIDceTrCYTc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Most items ordered were average. The Vongole was a disappointment, dry, and undercooked. The house made bread burnt and hard. Calamari was oily and underseasoned.  Service was okay. Small portions for the price. All the drinks were great. Overall, it was an average experience with average food. The paper menu was pretty dirty with grease and stains, which was a turn-off.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzMXK0DzOYgBwFpMDhLLRoVYDP4FsopS3PEShF\u0026fid=0x0:0xf80280c4edf81822"],"When":"2023-9-17"},{"Name":"Angie Hallam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDRnMNO_Dh94L5sS51oaWPDwXJ11mwKshglWP_qM8VGKfyd5Oo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What an amazing place. Dinner was so good. We had the calamari starter and it was to die for!  Then my hubby and I had the lamb shank with risotto. There are not words expressive enough to say how very good it was. I had tiramisu for dessert and my hubby had the donuts. The atmosphere was great. The service was just wonderful. Their spritzers are so delicious too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPV5lVJ2Ml32a890sChJL5pIIunZTmKzBFAoEkb\u0026fid=0x0:0xf80280c4edf81822"],"When":"2023-12-3"},{"Name":"Ken B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKi0UHEqvrtK9b7zXvBSni89V4qdFRQmlmzKuNqGFJ9iPTWGGw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A hidden gem, great spot for family reunions or date night. Cozy dining room and private rear patio. Food is fresh and high quality but the dome pizzas are exceptional. Prices are on the higher end side but with their service and high quality ingredients it’s worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkaN21ZfqPFep2L-fP35pJVDiThZrGVVzogSRJ\u0026fid=0x0:0xf80280c4edf81822"],"When":"2021-8-21"},{"Name":"Angel Claypool","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInCmqnFK0WQ5UkL5con4MyZ2CXnepe1BfBoPVhZubxkFygiA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I had lunch there on Remembrance Day. We shared a Fungi Pizza and the Chicken Pesto spaghetti. We were impressed with both. It was so nice watching the chef putting wood in the oven before making our pizza. The pasta was really tasty and served perfectly cooked. The staff were all really friendly and the service was great. What a great little hidden gem in Fort Langley.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2uWOCXA2ZIwv-imi-k6kp8nIh5xt7OHJt-QY0\u0026fid=0x0:0xf80280c4edf81822"],"When":"2023-11-12"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Brittany p","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_uB5pidsYHCWubmdLJVIBeDxWqVRtgg9BFxH33llAL1k3OQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stopped by to pick up some of their fabulous plant medicine jams. We ordered a bison cabbage roll soup and bannock to go, 3 jams, 1 bannock and butter and 1 bannock with blueberry lavender jam. Everything was delicious 😋!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOPlCBfUHr7Nex1IT5yuKZq2mbFMNRrWHshVH7&fid=0x0:0xa7657d78c5500181"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Alexa Blouin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDw57hgtPB0lGwZCH-Ubgklok7_HjV9d1e1xryqQmEJc-yxbk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super friendly owner and staff, such an amazing story in the news about their opening. The bannock was so delicious I drove 45 minutes to come to this place. Lemonade had a nice strong lemon taste not too sweet. Keep in mind this location is IN the fort right now so you have to pay entrance fee to visit this cafe. I look forward to visiting again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN07Ce9_3Jpu_ds5kxrDZunI_m4kMUFP2oczUk&fid=0x0:0xa7657d78c5500181"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Candice Neveu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXz90gRpK_I7vOiD4hkNm9KMJy06goRd3GrjbdUvYJ9P-Iv4YjlqA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to Fort Langley historic site specifically to visit this cafe, though the fort was a fun bonus. We were there close to closing (about 30min prior to) so had the place to ourself. I ordered Bannock with raspberry dandelion jam and raspberry lavendar lemonade. It was delicious! The cafe itself features vibrant art and little dried lavender sprigs on the tables. If we are back this way, I'd stop again and try the elk tacos I think.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNp4-Lqsfn2dCmKNsOJ5mQAPgTsWk8QoHF_bZ0S&fid=0x0:0xa7657d78c5500181"],"When":"2024-3-9"},{"Name":"Shelley Luce","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrrZJ8WSgN7RG_pbFTMdgLI9QWZf-J1dxvMGKw-7VvBLRBridJ8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I bought Tradish pear & chamomile jam at a market and it is delicious. More like a fruit preserve or compote - I put it on toast, on pancakes, in yogurt and also ate it from a spoon. So flavourful! I also have a jar of strawberry sweetgrass jam that I can't wait to try.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jenn C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocISDeZ5KmXrHWSDcHnnQ-eZKavUt9wPVuH8xv2iiFfPxARyhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The most delicious bannock! I also had an iced latte with a raspberry dandelion medicine shot. So good.  I will go back to the fort just so I can go here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alana P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLj1pdKTQd2gI1DCo6G1TcMIhhSZ1MCIphrXwmPNUw_vOHVX_Dh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My husband I came in to visit one Sat afternoon about 2 weeks ago. my husband purchased 3 coffee cups @ 30.00  he was thinking that cups were made for the cafe only   to find these exact same  cups 0n the ferry in their gift shop @ 14.99  (Beautiful cups)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brett Villeneuve","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfmVgMKEWPuQ9qPI3DkVvgqMI-Nu0lz5ao9rWx1KEE5kNl2HEY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered the bison and bannock at the food truck in East Van today, but what I got was a tex-mex chili with a few chunks of ground bison on bannock and a crazy handful of spring mix on the top. The bannock was good, but I wouldn't recommend this specific item as it was $23 and a big L for me. I'd suggest doing a pulled bison over ground bison and maybe change the flavor from tex-mex to spices used within the culture (rosemary, juniper, sage, sweetgrass, etc).
Edit/response: Thank you. I am aware of the three sisters, as I am Métis, but kidney beans (Peruvian), corn, and what I assumed was mushy squash chunks, and whatever spices used gave tex mex... for example, it was served with hotsauce, sour cream, and a handful of spring mix. I appreciate the offer to come in and eat something else, but I respectfully decline as I just don't think what you serve is up to my standards of dining. Best of luck to you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Laura Gannon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLEcMnSU13UNouU_JmQZVvkqA-ZrfSpVfi4_XQbDnDfepaahA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Unfortunately, we seem to have caught them at a bad time. We ordered 3 tacos and 3 lemonade. It took us close to 1/2 hour to get our food, even though they had no other orders they were serving at that time. Our bill with the tip was $93. I may not have provided a 20% tip, but you pay when you order so you tip out of courtesy, not knowing the type of service you may receive. Also, while we were sitting and waiting, other visitors to the Fort came in.  The person responsible for the till had gone in the back and, since there was no one at the till, these visitors waited a few minutes and then left.

The food was good although the portions on the vegetarian tacos were small. I will try them again when they've had a chance to gain some experience. But I do hope the service and the portion sizes improve.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lilesh K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZMp024jZfOBuM1XKJORf-SD1dPfa91bUxktaIyS4u5N8pRWs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a family dinner here, and we really enjoyed ourselves.  From the quality of food, and the exceptional service we were given
by Jenna and Danika. We will want to be back more often.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBXpHYsBYAo0yZl9vdmxqefdgY9dTDmqDNo7Fm&fid=0x0:0xfe5ec2724c2b37ac"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Barendina Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4gAXNw7bsOWNo-qAPQuFfFYX-uW_wVZHByRe8lPzJaAZZQQG6pQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"***Edit*** in order to respond to management reply.  NO, u are incorrect.  Piper, if that is who's taking responsibility, did not have a note pad when she took our orders.  In fact, I even mentioned, "Are u sure u can remember everyone's orders, & another waitress was also assisting.  Neither wrote anything down at our table, otherwise why would she need to come back to our table 3X to say "I'm sorry, but what did u order, or your meal comes with, sry forget to ask u, here are your choices"  There were several other things, I did not mention in review, because telling potential customers our waitress had to be asked 2x for our granddaughters chocolate milk, & forgotten strawberries & whip cream, toast ...I felt could be left out, but since excues are being made by u, I will include this in my edit.

Also, admitting that your staff overcharged us gratuity & not doing the right thing to rectify that is great for business, I bet, in addition to staff not being properly trained on that end of things.  Not to mention, staff telling potential customers wanting the buffet, who were wanting to make Mother's day reservations that YES your restaurant WAS doing Mother's day buffet & it was never the plan....terrible!  We chatted with several others waiting in line who were also told the same thing, only to arrive to no buffet, some even leaving when they found out...so your staff clearly dropped the ball.   We spent well over $200 at your establishment that day & all u do is defend staff mistakes, lie about what really happened, not offer any form of rectification for the  overcharge which could technically be classifiedas theft & fraud! Then u say u look forward to serving us again? 😉 We will not ever come back to this restaurant. Unethical behavior by management 100% that should be reported, which my husband will likely be addressing!   I hope those who read this review make sure if they do go to your restaurant, that they carefully look over their bill BEFORE paying, so they too don't get their hard earned $ taken, so it can go into your employees pockets.  I can't even imagine how many other tables Piper has done this too...terrible Honest mistake? Then management should offer the customer nothing less than :let us make it right:...end of story.  That is ethical & professional customer service, not how u handled things.  I am now changing my * to 1

VERY DISAPPOINTED today.  We called last week & asked if they would be doing Mother's Day buffet & were told "Yes," so we reserved a table for 8.  6 adults, 2 children.

Only to discover once arriving, they did NOT have a buffet at all.  We should have left right then, but obviously at that point with everyone being hungry & most other places likely booked, we stayed.  Waitress was ok, & she chose not to write our orders down, so she had to come back several times to  ask what we ordered again, forgetting several items as well. A few people at the table had issues with their meals. (not enough to complain)  I asked for no powdered sugar on my bread, but it was on it.  At the end of our meals, waitress brought our 5 separate bills.  At that time, we were slammed with the reality that there was an automatic 15% gratuity added to each of our individual bills.

That angered several people at our table.  #1. Tipping should not be forced upon anyone.  A tip is earned by hard work.  A tip is a customer's way of expressing appreciation for the effort the staff made to please you.  An expectation, absolutely, but certainly not mandatory.  So, to force that upon a customer is rude.  Also, some of our guests were single & still forced to pay the 15% gratuity without feeling they received a proper meal or service, not to mention, unaware of other guests also coming, so that upset them.

2. Our table should have been told this BEFORE ordering, not once she brought our bills to the table.  That is what upset me.

I'm always a generous tipper, but I would agree, I don't like feeling as though I'm being forced to tip.  It's not right, especially if the staff did not earn it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUz3TLYF_mEDcDWrm8fSmvb6RPHxvd1yox9iPN&fid=0x0:0xfe5ec2724c2b37ac"],"When":"2024-5-13"},{"Name":"Andreas Weigl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWesY7_o3e4JvTgrlkRe_dgu8tLW-XkKJYNq6H25z2Q0EPwOb1t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's one of my favourite restaurants. Love the food. I love the atmosphere. The staff is always friendly. The only negative is that they seem understaffed and it can take a bit. If you don't mind waiting or are on a date and enjoy the conversation then this is perfect.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZqUH4FukIQLnFgS1B61zWXmwsDM6MF3N53zPd&fid=0x0:0xfe5ec2724c2b37ac"],"When":"2024-5-21"},{"Name":"Cindy Woodman Patrick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLgwZiQDRJnusFKQcYd4yUtHopLhOMOajMw-H77_IRhsbsNIg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We arrived and were seated relatively quickly and served coffee. The waitress took a long time to take our order, and we waited for 45 min for our dinners. The waitress or hostess didn’t come back in all that time to top up coffee or water. The food tasted really good, but within my first few bites, I bit on a plastic bread tag! They gave me a choice of a new dinner, which I declined, and the waitress said they would take my meal off the bill. I had grab my own water during our meal. It was also very cold in the restaurant. Ricky’s please train your staff better!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdp3SI3aeHL4Ruo_PPk9ZmwyB7MedAyLunjwBY&fid=0x0:0xfe5ec2724c2b37ac"],"When":"2024-3-6"},{"Name":"Rick Kang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjOq61sPXRY_KPgAUkhVZPwBt5DllnQk6_dDzgEy4Pf7oXOA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for breakfast with Santa. It did not disappoint. Santa made multiple trips to our table and even sat down with us for about 10 mins to talk to us. It was great.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKLlY925xLltZQAU0w48n-yX9kEdjF5Z6RHZP9OehsSCFJ8rg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the first time I ordered from Ricky's in mission and I am really impressed! Portion size was massive and delicious! Staff there is really nice too 😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVp5whECzqd_8Z9-cxm8-YLosK5E_AHeveIoGX&fid=0x0:0xfe5ec2724c2b37ac"],"When":"2023-11-30"},{"Name":"sandra ferguson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSo7u7x7l34O3Ms54cvs0_IS_asSZk3He-UXd1IIGmJeE6UA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We really like going to Rick's. The host and server were prompt and very friendly. Could not have asked for better service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN8JYT6XgPvOKEN69Z1oBBJnHMCsfBeRwr5VoK&fid=0x0:0xfe5ec2724c2b37ac"],"When":"2022-2-27"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Corey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzhQB2BNI1Lxvhj9PIQtc-L6YW8U4iIXkOuC1hqavLbzFE-0k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"GET THE WINGS. Sticky, sweet, with a little bit of heat.

This place is phenomenal and we will make  another stop when we visit mission again!

They were also courteous enough to help us near closing time. Great family owned business that makes top quality food to eat in or to go!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOr8oBP8X1MAM4SroQ2zDm6UB5F45rPgKS5hg0m&fid=0x0:0x12ef2cd6d2ebe591"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Chloe Yakashiro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVF9PzRQh9I6D9LnEshiz0VsAp47engFl8IErtbj36K6gvScw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This the first time we have been to the restaurant since it moved. And this is NOT the same Embers it used to be. It may be the same name, but the food is completely different. The burgers were pre made patties with some sort of filler, perhaps they were Costco patties? They are no longer on homemade buns or home made wraps like still advertised in the menu. The staff was super friendly when we came to pick up tho, they are are not lacking there. Unfortunately we will not be returning here again  as I would say the food is equal to a cafeteria style serving now.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHgp6jelwuN6Of1hdDy7JwdPnUt0W9iIbC13Jp&fid=0x0:0x12ef2cd6d2ebe591"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"Kristin Kiyon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLo1wkdi0Zzb0vAMvjEJeWZ8SBNIxOS6IhJc2-03mByjRvwbA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We love going to Embers! The service and food is always exceptional and they have a nice little patio as well. If you are looking for the tastiest BBQ food in mission you have to try this place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0yKaqKJe4_SqeJJVwWzR6Dd3PwQZTaHSGwm3b&fid=0x0:0x12ef2cd6d2ebe591"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Roxy S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgDOKdyZCgI_oAo2Qe6kuJQYOm9EVxgrpoII03kM_NBt7pcM6d=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great BBQ place for takeout or dine in, with patio option. Location isn't super obvious and feels tucked away. Neighbours to a tattoo parlour. Kid's menu is top notch, and my boys loved the grilled cheese and burger. Crayons were fresh, good colour variety, and choice of activities or colouring for entertainment while food was being prepared. I split the mini sampler with my partner to experience as many options as possible. Hot wings were that slow burn, sweet sauce. Hotter than Frank's red hot sauce, not too hot for me. I recommend choosing the dark chicken option, the white breast was on the dry side, but good paired with the pulled pork or extra sauce from the wings or baked beans. Ribs are fall off the bone and easy to split with a butter knife. The beef brisket was a little disappointing - served in too much water. Would have been better on the grilled bun with beans. Pulled pork was the star, I recommend anything with it. Oh, and the mixed green salad was a great light side with lots of dried fruit. Lots of leftovers to take home! The fries were fresh and thick cut.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUBj7o7oNCJpVa2UQTpSjJU61lkBc5KDmA9Ibp&fid=0x0:0x12ef2cd6d2ebe591"],"When":"2023-7-2"},{"Name":"Johnny Tesoro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXl0z5UrXy7DtSiVKAyHZslENo41U9QguL3sVxgVXv1pqqfxPY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It's not bad. If you are looking to have your bbq meats smoked, then you will be disappointed...especially with the Brisket which is braised and served in a very thin liquid meant to be au jus (lacks flavor). The pulled pork is seasoned with cumin which seems to be trying to cover up a lack of flavor and dryness. The baked beans were tasteless so you should avoid this side. The pork ribs were pretty good. They meat falls off the bone nicely and the bbq sauce is tasty. The chicken lacks smoke and tastes like regular rotisserie chicken.
The overall presentation of the platter is good and there is a lot of food.The wings were good with a nice honey garlic flavor. The caesar salad is fresh and delicious and the fries and bread were very nice. Fat wedges and generous buttery portions respectively.
The service is attentive and friendly. The dill potato salad is excellent! But speaks to how everything is nontraditional. If I were to come back, I'd have the ribs with potato salad again with caesar salad and fries.
The restaurant was very clean as well. Embers is not a traditional bbq house. So don't expect a Memphis, Texas or Carolina style bbq restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOd5n8E4d-kh6VfQd2bhaOoYPCxlTxZ0pGnEmOn&fid=0x0:0x12ef2cd6d2ebe591"],"When":"2021-9-22"},{"Name":"Allee Gaede","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqqx3JtVzKeIpo6kcou60NIzL0a5YHGuJlw4xHO3jjcBl3Sg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My husband and I decided to try Ember and wow! It was good! I got Pulled pork sandwich, my husband got the firehouse burger and my daughter got the kids cheese burger. Great price, and great portions! We'll definitely be going back! Oh and we ordered cornbread so delicious","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMK1a3w8vhga_p6yJJEOv7aFYmOsA8mcbEFcA1W&fid=0x0:0x12ef2cd6d2ebe591"],"When":"2022-10-27"},{"Name":"Susy S.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOXFRmPNhvtrh6EsN703ph8OLmY1L5EksqjupPcRZsoEiF39uMiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We heard about Embers from a friend and decided to try it out. We orders the pulled pork poutine, Jordan Burger and the Beef Dip. Only 4 stars because I really didn't like the spices used in the pulled pork, but that is just me. It was a very strong acidic flavour & cumin flavour. I like my pulled pork a little more mellow. But the fries and gravy ... OMG ... Our son said the fries were the best he's ever had. The beef in the beef dip was tender and had flavour, but was a little dry. The portions were good. The poutine is enough for two. It's a nice stop, and you can social distance on the patio.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4-RfTsbsYXQ9jDphGxHVFOWbMPX67WbUZ1GSB&fid=0x0:0x12ef2cd6d2ebe591"],"When":"2020-9-13"},{"Name":"Kelvin L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIKP-AEz_-4OsWq_LkU6jY6VsViU-g2T1snkyr7uxb8Q5hpgcQGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Decided to give Embers BBQ House a try after doing a search for restaurants near Mission Raceway. Ordered the Micheal Sandwich with fries...it was a very good bbq chicken sandwich. The hand cut fries were awesome too.
The service was good too.
A hidden little gem!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm3ZDbD6kNmXKdO_yTeCOgJmEKUT5ExoZywey-&fid=0x0:0x12ef2cd6d2ebe591"],"When":"2022-6-24"}]

[{"Name":"Joey Berezanski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOPJevacCQOMcpP_OO2JYMps2lAWumv8LiRYnWJhisFZl-sOws_A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The beef yaki udon has got to be the best I’ve ever had.  Literally drank the left over sauce in my bowl. The beef is very thinly shaved, tender and seems like a lot of beef comparatively. I will be back here for sure. Good service and atmosphere too. Very clean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDe9rvO_Ol2wpARllF5hSD-C2RNwZFx8fgh1YY&fid=0x0:0x8443932ed0e0dd05"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Benzi Schnauzer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUg4Da1Z4WzIs-k4nrBAmbrswcwf-49CVVRmHpcw6VLF6kUyoZl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great meal at Sushi Hinode.  When in Fort Langley, this is where we would recommend you go for modern Japanese food in a relaxed environment.

Service was attentive and friendly.  We were seated in the middle of this relatively small restaurant and took advantage of the opportunity to people watch.  Our waiter answered our questions and our order arrived quickly.

The restaurant is modern, maintained, and clean.  Active cleaning and sanitizing was taking place between seatings, which is nice to see.  There is a honey pine and warm white colour palette at play here, which is relaxing and modern.

The food was delicious and well presented.  The fish was fresh without any indication of sitting too long.  The sushi rice had an exceptionally nice balance of sweet and tart, which caught our attention as something we enjoyed.  Portions were generous; but not cut into pieces that are more than a mouthful (a problematic habit at other sushi establishments).

I recommend Sushi Hinode.  I can't criticize anything about our experience and we will be returning customers.  It is worth both your time and money.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMo7EFJ_QppugyiIYal5HWpbrf50Jeofa6tY9To&fid=0x0:0x8443932ed0e0dd05"],"When":"2023-5-28"},{"Name":"Sean Fernando","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV--UQylT0NU5pJsdy1oVpNzJnrF-a9wppc1WThGoEFMAG8s9wn1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Can't believe I didn't some here sooner. Really enjoyed our dinner tonight. Had the squid karaage which was well seasoned, light and crispy.
The sushi was fresh and the Nigiri pieces were nice and long,  the Tuna was especially soft and delicious. I'll definitely be back, everything we had tonight was great, looking forward to trying the other menu items.
Also, staff is very attentive and working with big smiles. Cozy atmosphere with nice big windows.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMi-Bmy1vtmIA0wmGloWJKacMKtyQfEJiImYr7E&fid=0x0:0x8443932ed0e0dd05"],"When":"2022-12-25"},{"Name":"Amar M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBQWZODVOR5EgW_ud4WGBoPZzS3E7_T_DuyVRfFsnuGSHVIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Never a bad experience here.  Small spot, great service and great chef.  Locals know, and are regulars.  Speciality rolls and spicy options are amazing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOB9QlZ0xrqXDZKb0umTZ-7_MO8x6IanMuZrfr6&fid=0x0:0x8443932ed0e0dd05"],"When":"2024-2-16"},{"Name":"Yui Chit Jiff Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-uUyC4o_20rrkv3nCKHjaAwDrVoN7ihm8gdC7o5yMrUXzfOg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best Japanese food I have eaten in my life. The portion sizes and are huge, and the food is tasty too! The stars of the shows are the lunch plates, as they had a soup , squid balls, rice and chicken or beef. And only for 18 dollars? Best deal ever. Would come here every time when coming to Fort Langley.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Arugula","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfskdG3gPQfjcZCkJkHF0tc1mtATONBAaeETvFMjVPCrfkz9eH1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very fresh and delicious sushi.
The place is very clean and nice ambiance.
The service was great.
It was my first time dining in this restaurant but I will be back.
I really recommend this sushi place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZ-B_t8Vueyd4apyjvEZ_yvEk2zB6p3JucwaHJ&fid=0x0:0x8443932ed0e0dd05"],"When":"2022-5-13"},{"Name":"Leila Lewis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtEnW3aas8I3sbd5is-LFt93xAV43qKYLv0wgSbXOWrxMfSkatuw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was the first time I went to sushi hinder in a long time, but I forgot how good it is! Menu is vast! We had edamame, sushi mango roll and some udon soups, which were all fantastic, fresh and delicious! Prices were quite reasonable. It’s a small location, but finding a seat was no problem on a Saturday night!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kate Burton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEsYnXVElD0WqZTT2irRDUv3iOd79yjZUR7Q6y8oDmATRDcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Rolls full of rice, and the tiniest sliver of fish on the top - apparently enough to charge 15$ for the roll. Rice not seasoned, black and flavourless, in the tuna roll fish was warm, chicken udon has a nice flavour to the sauce, but barely any chicken. It used to be a good spot, I don’t know what happened to it","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Oluwayomi Adebule","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXqcIg8ujO4XiC50cD8_FM6q8RuvnCHkeqVI4f08BodMBvibbJTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had the premium Colleen’s Breakfast which consists of 2 thick bacon, 2 Farmer’s sausages and 2 free range eggs. Served with hash browns and toast. Service was warm and great. Ambience was of a trucker’s stop with license plates from all over plastered on the walls. Seems to be a neighborhood favorite as the customers appear to be recurring customers. Lookin go to try some of the lunch specials next","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmU8zIEXeH9YOaa9aUmMVV37Wu883GzB9fo89Q&fid=0x0:0xc71fc105e2bc39fe"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"LC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKgKXDcGIDcbkesef0FqudeAjvBmr8QtlNItEK7Lr5yWNkI3w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a hidden gem in the area. Really friendly staff. They remember guests' names and know what their favorite foods are. The wonderful vintage decorations make you feel like you are eating a meal prepared by your mom at home. Farmer's Skillet and Everything Omelette are really generous and delicious for the price. The coffee served right away is really fresh. I will 1000% plan to visit again next time.
You must eat their homemade white bread. It is soft and really delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7dd-Su-cqx4isJIGAleW-hhJ9JC4nwuPbEACB&fid=0x0:0xc71fc105e2bc39fe"],"When":"2024-7-23"},{"Name":"Teka winder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrg_EKkzojLLLoMU7Bf0z0zU_rycbl-LUhWVQc5FPzUTBMBepG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is one of the absolute best cafe's I have ever been too. The staff is so friendly and the food is out of this world delicious and beautiful! Made with passion and love! The decor is awesome.
