user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Gen X Surrey Girl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnz98iwXPE1DskfLpfNg-zDV5mDy1tGmvmbNcHWdRqf6q4OTmNvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not the greatest Chinese food. Our usual place was closed on Monday so we gave this one a try. The prices were much lower than other places. We were looking for a bargain but now we see you get what you pay for.

The food tasted like curry. I don't know if it's intentionally added. Is this a fusion restaurant? Or is it cross-contamination? I like Curry but not in my Chinese food. It was a real turn off. Some of my family members refuse to eat it because of this.

The Chow Mein noodles are not edible. They were so soggy. No one liked them. Really gummy.  And they were cut into 2 inch pieces. Who does this. I like long proper noodles. I don't like having it cut up like it's for a baby.

Almond chicken was ok but nothing special.

Honey garlic pork was good.

BBQ pork fried rice had gnarly bits of fat instead of meat. The bits weren't edible. It was nasty. This dish also had heavy Indian seasoning. Again, not sure if this was intentional or if they don't wash their dishes well and there is some cross-contamination. My family hated the rice.

Beef chop suey. Very gnarly meat. Had to spit it out.

Ginger beef. Really, really mushy. So unappealing. Isn't Ginger beef supposed to be crispy?

Wonton soup. Had a very weird taste. Did not like the broth. Whatever the ingredient was it was overpowering.

Spring Rolls tasted odd. Family wouldn't eat them after the first bite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLUAn93dpnpZJ7pmF43FvSZh8nOljc5P11NiQ1&fid=0x0:0x1a544fea7bc5d4f7"],"When":"2024-3-18"},{"Name":"Deb Johnson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkedR6SI-JhZPJCsIcMr058cfIHTo5ZFP-uLbUws23bwH-Ng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is supposed to be a 4 combo...they have a new server...she a young girl with blond curly hair and a massive nasty attitude...she made us wait for 10 minutes for an item to cook...that's fine but she dished up the rest of the order and put it on the the counter by the sink to get it out of the way...we asked her if management has started cut backs on orders...she says you get what you get...when the rest of the order was done the rest of the order was cold...the other 2 servers had packed the containers right full...they weren't even very busy...if this is the type of employee they are hiring then we won't be back and we've been coming here for years🤬🤬🤬","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQ19k2mnEkePHjYBq4LL4Ary_dtydGveqw3XwO&fid=0x0:0x1a544fea7bc5d4f7"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"Aleksander Amer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGOAz6hZJ2NwhTQXXReoo8ipuBBnVUyRU2feoLZjGgiTMM8r_W=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I was a walk in and got the 4 item combo. Really big portion you can eat for a few days for $20. I got curry chicken, ginger beef, S n S pork on chow mein. I chatted with Tammy and she is awesome. Friendly and didn’t rush me. Highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO308q0pi8xdQGXQat4OqmJ_D5a4JkD7tWPNAo4&fid=0x0:0x1a544fea7bc5d4f7"],"When":"2023-10-3"},{"Name":"Ryan Chambers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJk3hPfgAVU14mzJPwix2VAPW7rNq8VRQZB1Mq-d2PNWi1PdA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Tried to upcharge for a substituted item after payment was made . Instead of being decent and saying . Well now you know for next time they wouldn't budge over $5. So I got a refund and went to HOT WOK which was cheaper and way better. Will never be back. Over $5.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Courtney Byrne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoKDeTQRF5Kex_sjcrAreCZ-az5MzpEjk7CuY3_emaT3ZpjBAF=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ok first time ordering here and I took my first bite of my dinner and it was the “dry garlic pork” and my first taste was curry…???  This qas over top of my rice which made that taste of curry as well. First time in my life ordering Chinese food and it did NOT taste as it was Chinese food. The rest of our food was fine but totally not what you’re expecting and that flavour just finds takes over the whole meal. So one and done. I tried but not again. Oh and the wonton soup did not taste like wonton soup.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tammy Nimmo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYlpOTPPpVD_OSv8riaTX1_ZkMzDwesELpyTfrTzNdXc40KQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food is decent but service is absolutely ridiculous! Placed an online order said it was 50 min...showed up and waited an additional 30 minutes! Food wasn't even ready, they were more concerned about walk in customers then anyone who placed an online order. Absolute chaos and this is not the first time this has happened. They are now filling the lid of the take out containers instead of the base which is substantially smaller so your getting way less which a couple people commented on and the girl said absolutely nothing and their deep fried wonton have 1/4 tsp of filling and looks more like a chip and is so small that you actually can't taste the filling","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfeYs44Ae_zp_9nfl-Sj3n1mqRdyEdAhpYTo8a&fid=0x0:0x1a544fea7bc5d4f7"],"When":"2023-4-23"},{"Name":"James Afuan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMX9y4YIit6QnsHkgmhtESBQf5hEnvr3eL-OoFA84fJi0CtOlp=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Gil and Manny were nice, smiling, approachable and had great customer service when I always go there. Always greet and says how's my day going! Overall foods are great and delicious!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Simon Vandenberg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLUqMms88AaVErnh59mp5AIKcXIGNoGl5Qkdx-rTvnyaZfJjg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The wonton soup is good but I waited 40+ minutes for my soup","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBoapDz1C_VvcF9Qogbj29jKnujDc-QkxFni_q&fid=0x0:0x1a544fea7bc5d4f7"],"When":"2024-11-12"}]

[{"Name":"Rosie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJz4H1tL3T9Bs6UQSB5pP6-85rCn7xVEwV4-7OXBlfK_rocGA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The veggie burger is really gross.. it didn’t say anywhere on the menu that it is plant based beyond meat patty nor did the server bother telling us. The fries were bland. The pizza was very basic.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYsual9LbvyUtgYFItW7_d8KMrZWP8q6KpxVX9&fid=0x0:0x9e93e0082ded47ff"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Jonathan Ness","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKPCFY4JGn3TEXvjrrXiRcfBV4_OtWqyuNk-FxAmgEiR_ZZss=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We walked by this place earlier in the day and saw gluten free pasta on the menu posted outside.  We decided to come back later for dinner based on the menu.  When we came back to order, they turned out to no longer have pasta.  The slices of pizza at the counter looked to have been there for quite a while. We ordered a gluten free pizza and a regular pepperoni pizza.  My daughter didn't love the GF pizza (she left a review too...). I thought the regular pepperoni pizza was pretty good - we enjoyed it!  The crust is pretty thick.  So if you don't like thick crust, don't come here.  But I liked it.  Probably wouldn't come here a second time but definitely ok pizza.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"levi legroulx","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWmXvOg0MFCdqXdKYJ0mLdmmlZJInYXGYeNljjHaN7voMDKHvsH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Pizza is bad. I grabbed a slice and I'm pretty sure it had been sitting there all day. The crust was so tough I couldn't bite through it. Unfortunately, the staff member did not wash her hands  after using the til before grabbing my slice and whipped apart with her finger. I recommend fraser health to come and visit. Would not recommend and will not be returning","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cassandra Souter Williams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTlrxIAXgKHMz8BjIsWK-NQpYVGGHbBPvLqKAD4N-dKdqlOm3NSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Service. Terrible, everyone looked miserable and took so long for drinks and food. After about an hour of waiting for our pizza it still wasn’t cooked through and tasted like it was under a heat lamp got 30 minutes. And it was terrible pizza …This restaurant ruined our experienced… don’t go..","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Natalia Ludwig","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbRFOTW9XoLdrsLj2t-TDvwFje3CumaoMfh0q57HNM27HIBEDy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely horrible. Pizza was soggy and undercooked, rats were everywhere, food and safety regulations were in no way met, staff doesn’t wash their hands or wear gloves and were very unfriendly and unprofessional, food took FOREVER, and the place was generally dirty. Would never eat here again and suggest no one else does either.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sarah Hansen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWz4mG1Py5nh3lv1SnEXOYRhIAmvufQDycLVQSjzj4dQ5F3vVlcVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We stopped in for a slice of pizza and although cheap at 2.50 a slice…
This pizza is a very small slice, the staff was friendly but after walking from the back and cashing us out at the till. She grabbed the slice of pizza with her bare hands and plunked it on a plate. Very unsanitary when we didn’t see her wash her hands. I would suggest some tongs to grab the pizza.
Won’t be returning.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jordan van Dijk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJc3hhX7otvtGBP-CmGLUj1nn7KPdMmIieUqYkTO4ozTju1cXw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Pretty awful pizza and awful service.

They confirmed our order and charged us through the online ordering, and when I got there to pick up the food, the wings I ordered weren't there. When I questioned where they were the only guy working the joint said "oh yeah, we don't have any so I refunded you." I looked at th records and there is no evidence of a refund. I called later and the guy said it might be 3 or 4 business days for the refund to show up.

So not only do we have the amount of food we planned for dinner, we now need to monitor for a refund.

The pizza itself quite bad.

The pepperoni pizza tastes like Chuck E Cheese's. Just a few slices of pepperoni, oily cheese, a little cheap tomato sauce and a poorly cooked crust.

The pierogi pizza is crazy. I think they forgot half the ingredients. No evidence of the green onions or chili flakes that the menu suggests. I don't think there was sour cream either. The potato slices were raw and crunchy. The cheese WAY overloaded. The crust was a sponge of oil.

The only saving grace was the cheese tasted flavourful near the edge of the crust. The one good but of the meal I guess.

The amount of grease was insane. My first slice of pizza fell apart due to its mushy greasiness.

I've just had a slice of each and my stomach is now gurgling. Gotta run to the bathroom bye","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jonathan Dolan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4h1_b_v9o8yLp2IkJuBVFfhKwQiyNxXAkCB7Hhee3Wxg8kxVzaw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Really disappointed in this pizza. It was really doughy and just did not taste good. Both my wife and I not only did not finish our pizzas, we ordered two smalls, but we couldn't even get though two pieces! We threw the rest away and we are not the type of people to waste food like that. It honestly tasted like the pizza had been reheated or something because the consistency of the cheese had a certain "previously cooked yet not melted enough" feel in the mouth. Kinda gooey but in a bad way. The pizzas are not cheap either. When you spend almost 20 bucks on a SMALL pizza, you'd expect it to be amazing!  Definitely, would not recommend.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food with a great selection of books! We came on a weekend, which was crowded with people lining up for food, which was certainly worth it! They have a nice portion size, with some delicious drinks to go with. I highly recommend their grilled cheese and shrimp pasta :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPILYzI7w-n_5BmAlABIdy83mOGEWt-vv4pJ_Vz&fid=0x0:0x2ef72d1dd313a292"],"When":"2024-12-25"},{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The café had an inviting atmosphere, and the staff were absolutely amazing—friendly, attentive, and eager to make the experience enjoyable. However, the food left something to be desired. I ordered the chocolate cake and the cheese scone, but unfortunately, both were stale. While the texture was disappointing, the richness of the chocolate flavor was actually very good, which salvaged the dessert a bit. I also ordered a latte that was okay. Overall, I had a mixed experience—great service, but the quality of the sweets could use improvement. Would still return for the ambiance and hospitality!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3kXu4yONvJUHT_HCLoS7VDmDWPtRXNdKdqYg9&fid=0x0:0x2ef72d1dd313a292"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Jordan Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW11-xeEA0Ih57ocfphXt0C50QwI614ll6t2qknklEqHoDt3aVy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A nice cafe and bookstore with some good good options for brunch, though very limited table space to sit and eat. The short rib mac and cheese on special was pretty good, and what I believe was the Thai coconut curry soup was decent. A simple solid option for food in the area, with a neat bookstore area to browse as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHzOquZzu58zMEjh7qGHK4OuZlVQ8Rv_phoMIs&fid=0x0:0x2ef72d1dd313a292"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Gerry A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVtoo7d9k-jl8g8Olh4q9lMKjWQOCXf8VHpTk3fUjsRUEkuuL-pA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came here for lunch and were able to get a nice table outside.   Pro-tip: you can find your seat outside scan the barcode order at your table and they will bring it out to you!     This will save you having to wait in line and avoid the temptation of all the beautiful and delicious cakes and pies.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTvvzWohNQ3sDC30O0zigGZOh34eoWV-W0gGYc&fid=0x0:0x2ef72d1dd313a292"],"When":"2024-8-28"},{"Name":"Dani D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOGG8I4GIq7TGLsN0IQW0rGa_W6AS9VgHWmtPmBvQMWKi_VP1s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute place for breakfast and brunch, easy to grab a sandwich and a coffee on the way to school and work. Sitting down is another story because my table was very close to the cash register so people were constantly behind me. The Avocado Benny barely had avocado.. but the oatmeal was good. Also, two people in my party got their meal just under 10 minutes before me and another person got our oatmeal.. so maybe ask for all the food to come out together?

Enjoyed the experience and the food regardless.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5B8rWeb9rwImPxzxqmyuac3FHC3nnkPEUjbdo&fid=0x0:0x2ef72d1dd313a292"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"Luna Yoon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrSWH180GU0prt7Q02XLGOunXawSpGLg-4tuh-HUvyxrXPOjZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sooo good, I didn't expect that much but it was really good. Even in the morning time and week day, still many line up for taking order. I couldn't ordered that chicken wrap because it's not lunch time yet.
I would like to try next time.
I ate there and take out for my bf.
Becasue I really want him try this place food.
I will come back 100%","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9dmerpiNWfrQqKDTIBaqaPF03ijKRAgkk69d0&fid=0x0:0x2ef72d1dd313a292"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went to Wendel’s Bookstore & Cafe hoping to grab some lunch, but the line was almost out of the door and it was way too busy on a Saturday. We came back later in the afternoon to grab some coffee and dessert and it was still busy so we gave up. We did check out the small bookstore section though, which was nicely organized. But it did feel a bit clusterphobic with the queue and diners eating near the entrance and we didn’t stay long.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2PVKaWHyB4cVKJpKb_SfIBWkvEBiCqU_aBJhs&fid=0x0:0x2ef72d1dd313a292"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"MiCap19 nerd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWR0O1WpksEG8SnIbTdyAuIebW4CtfJmRwbqcUOCwM6bvDmtNnu8g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great desserts, drinks, and atmosphere. I especially love the connecting Bookstore.  It's always fun. It can get cold in the fall sitting anywhere near the doors, but still a nice place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzt7cvXTD1TwTnQlSnI-Yly1MjhBRkPnS1GaNe&fid=0x0:0x2ef72d1dd313a292"],"When":"2024-10-7"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Brittany S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eFQkj626t8zGBNhG1j682nXYAY3vJkS1VdBBUNRvZlKC0L6p=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had my first experience here today and I will for sure be back! To start - I don't prefer alcohol beverages but hubby loves his beer and breweries.

The bartender was great. He greeted when we walked in. They seemed a bit short with I believe one server. She was okay but could have been a bit more friendly (was not rude just could have upped her energy a little). The basics were done - checked in on us made sure we weren't waiting on anything else.

So! Hubby ordered the Sunday special which was a pint of beer and the soft pretzel with dip of choice. He asked for the Light Speed Pale Ale which he mentioned was quite nice.
We shared the pretzel and requested queso as the dip. 10/10 best soft pretzel and queso we have tried at a brewery by far. There were also a couple pieces of cut up dill pickle to dip. Amazing.

Now.. I'm a bit different. I knew I was getting a craft soda but I was hoping for a miracle drink that I was ready to make myself. On their dessert menu is ice cream and within their beverage menu is the Phillips root beer. You know where I'm going this. Their bartender made it happen for me. I sat at our table sipping my root beer alcohol free drink happier than I have ever been at a brewery.

To end our drinks we shared The Dutton hot dog. Now the dog itself is fairly basic but the toppings help quite a bit! Toppings were quite yummy and the banana peppers didn't have the heat I was anticipating but it was quite a nice mix of ingredients.

We will be back for sure. Hopefully for another root beer float if they're up for it but doo wanna try their other hot dogs. I may test a few beers if I'm feeling adventurous.

Atmosphere is darker side / was a bit warm inside. But seemed very fun with some couches set up and there's also board games on shelving between couch set up's (there's 2 sets of couches / tables for games etc)

Also in the ladies washroom the stall beside the sink is very very open with a gap between the door and wall... Just something to be mindful about.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDFjzi8iNf4aLYaahujvuQ6eAwUQBjcWHyxH3I&fid=0x0:0x35c03053a20596b2"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Sophie Gray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL36Qb7H0T0AWP0NY24K80_D5qPIl_SZUJgkywhO5EqMMBuSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5 stars all around. Had a tasting flight and all the beers were awesome. Also had pork and chicken tacos and corn ribs and they were perfect!  Great atmosphere and super friendly staff","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Garth Graham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYWzTGBmFbiQSoiP8BVngaDd93UKchEl26qOaKAYHo-ULIKPc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just finished our quarterly business meeting that we hosted at HUBco during the day. Escaped our stuffy meeting room and enjoyed an amazing atmosphere, great food, and cold beer when business was done. Our team left super happy, accomplished a ton, and we'll all be back for sure. Nice work HUBco!! You're onto something here, amazing meeting venue 😊❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0Ql2E1-hZXiRWC1NBq2bnwQ3_odf7nycPhtoq&fid=0x0:0x35c03053a20596b2"],"When":"2024-3-29"},{"Name":"Tatiana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLB8hhQhWdab10zfsKmQTePTm0vaF3fWaIdB-lR77yYaVZ47A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Cute place, I come here a lot....or at least I used to. My favorite staff all seem to be gone, and new people aren't as knowledgeable or friendly. The guy behind the bar can come off as rude at times and few of the new servers don't smile very often. Menus isn't huge so it can get old quick, but what you do order is usually good.
Service is slower than it used to be and place just seems....different.
Might find a different watering hole.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angie Holubowich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvA01uwV-ljjqyU9Lh65DooQQ-n5LGLqHoxdNvFbIabAvSWO6ShQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The ambiance in this space is off the charts. What a beautiful place for a drink or dinner. I would imagine attending one of their games or trivia nights are awesome.

I ordered the margarita, and my partner ordered the Cashmere Lager. The marg caught me off guard because of the prickly pear, but it was so refreshing. The beer was good, not hoppy and very light.

We ordered the pretzel with queso. Queso was good but could have been a little spicier. The pretzel was nicely salted and may have been overcooked just a twitch because it was a bit tougher than expected.

I ordered the tacos, one of each. The pork was good but needed the hot sauce. The sweet potato was delicious and heavy on the mayo. The  Korean chicken was the best. It's very wet and full of flavor.

My partner got the What's Hub Dog. Holy God. This thing was LOADED and a heck of a mess to eat, but it was worth every little bit.

We committed to the browned butter chocolate chip cookie in a pan before we were totally done with our food. Our meal was so filling we did not need it, but it was so so good. The perfect amount of ice cream for the cookie.

Would absolutely go again to try the Flatbread. Someone near us got one, and it looked amazing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNo5XAGEu7YA1Y1jouQxgDAEru77MoT2Q3vwZjC&fid=0x0:0x35c03053a20596b2"],"When":"2023-7-13"},{"Name":"M B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlMMyCIzsrVoW8CB6uuQ7oVZCKQe88hVJc4drkkkOtAZj68G-4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really love this place. Super friendly staff, great beer and the food is great. Nacho maker uses the "layer technique" which ensures cheese on nearly every chip instead of just on the top and then sad, lonely chips underneath that I find at most places. Pork tacos are delicious as well. Have tried a bunch of the hot dogs and can recommend them too.  I could go on about a few other things I had but don't want to overdo it and seem like a Homer. Buuuut the BBQ Chicken Flatbread was my fave. I ate most of it and forgot to take a pic of its full glory.

They have live music and TVs for the game. Place is well laid out with an upper and lower level and the typical brewery games on hand. We travel from Ridge to visit and will continue to do so.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIr3uk5z0bZnuuCSHZWeEdQZ7Hhuu7UijpZEVx&fid=0x0:0x35c03053a20596b2"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"Kathryn Syssoloff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLarp6XI_FKSs9NGNBlBzNZbH1_q7DcXHWBOT64Bs5NTJ9MZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today, our first visit to Hub for lunch!  I ordered the Chicken Tortilla Salad and it was huge and utterly gorgeous.  My hubby ordered the Smashed Burger and Caesar Salad and he loooooved it.  Beautiful service!  Hub has now become our go-to place.  It was relaxing, comfy and the decor so well done.  See ya soon!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nadine T (audichick)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXA3177BxZFROCKqw-oMDfqAzmQQJ6H7H1RyHULT0pjZraaZ9VZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"After looking at the reviews, we dropped in for the first time looking for somewhere to have a casual/pubstyle lunch. It has a cool brewery atmosphere. You can go upstairs or stay down. Pretty friendly staff! Our waitress unfortunately couldn't quite get our order right, and there was 2 of us. We both ordered a flight. I will say they had a decent selection, most of the ones we tried were pretty good. We both looked over the menu, and felt it fell quite short of decent choices. Settled on a beef dip. It was a bit disappointing. Although it had curb appeal, it wasn't all that great tasting. If you're heading here for a beer, check em out! If you are thinking of stopping in for a meal... I'd probably keep looking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDfGznfdk3qEzsXmjdzeQ9c3XXRYut98x8V2mz&fid=0x0:0x35c03053a20596b2"],"When":"2023-4-11"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"amrita upreti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEb7N6mSPNOhlnBGrLc_zqo_MofMZHg8KdY9FfMSHnPETyMaAUzQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Oh! Finally found it. Had been looking for chole bhature ever since we moved to metro Vancouver and this place is it.
Perfect food, steaming hot bhatura, yummy chole.
Mona is such a warm person, feeds you like family, in this small homely place. ♥️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyYe9Dg_cBvx4zGzffMTTYGPqFVPLedCrvlrBa&fid=0x0:0x989223df5dbaf36a"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"Tania Arora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCZQnKkf5XKXKfmvBa87h6HPQ-B-S7qQXSjKj21ACfbMU34ZFlYQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Drove to this restaurant all the way from burnaby and tried their Chhole Bhature and Momos—and they were absolutely amazing! The Chhole Bhature had the perfect balance of spices, and the Bhature was fluffy and crispy, just the way it should be. The Momos were equally delicious, with juicy fillings and a mouth-watering chutney to pair. Delhi style!

The owners were incredibly warm and welcoming, making the dining experience even better. If you’re looking for authentic Indian flavors and a great atmosphere, this place is a must-try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi8O1kv7jFjyEqFtpnf3wfmOBDjKTWrHC6rSBf&fid=0x0:0x989223df5dbaf36a"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Vikesh Garg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAaze0R7b9tIjeupgHrxFLvDdP8Bo-7D_GVNiJSygvoGzR6BKl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Chole Bhature is a standout dish that encapsulates the essence of Indian comfort food. The chole, rich and aromatic, boasts a perfect blend of spices, creating a flavorful experience that lingers on the palate. The bhature, light and fluffy, is golden-fried to perfection, providing a delightful contrast. Served with a side of tangy pickles, this dish is both satisfying and indulgent. The generous portion size ensures a fulfilling meal. Overall, Truly India delivers an authentic taste that makes this classic dish a must-try for anyone craving a taste of home","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPPvTeeqvhaS7NqFxS2zX_Kf_SPcpxc1RRZ-b3&fid=0x0:0x989223df5dbaf36a"],"When":"2024-10-2"},{"Name":"Jasreet Deol","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLOjxN2mXuaJcuPcbZLIuriWLP2-OWY6BAZCRXpEudQ-BbVtjT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Highly recommend. Amazing taste and Mona is so friendly. She takes care of customers like her own. Bhature chole are a must try. Just like India. Definitely go and try them! I’m
Looking forward to my next visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeZMtKux6lq-xA6M4jkH2nLF1hxCgBYa467Xs2&fid=0x0:0x989223df5dbaf36a"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Catarina Moreno","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWv4JQY9bfLLg5NkLH93Q4pnDX1JBRQxPKPzL8ztU0spUFEMw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a gem! We are visiting in the area and were checking what was around and landed here by accident. The food was delicious, freshly made and the owners of this family-run place are just lovely! My malai kofta was served decorated with flower petals and was excellent ❤️ definitely recommended and we will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMRXgNUktS9XiMrCSRQ1JCMNlZNXenSek7n-Bo&fid=0x0:0x989223df5dbaf36a"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Tanya Dawar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKJt557S0J-89SdnLK33fYTwcEvg908ZWuJmwdJ00iuYX7as0U=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very satisfied with the meal and service—highly recommend! If you’re craving Delhi’s Sita Ram’s chole bhature, visit this place. While they didn’t have bhature when I called, they served us Chole Kulche and their chole tasted just like Sita Ram Diwan Chand’s.😍 The head chef, a lady who works there with her husband, was very generous and even checked in with us. I suggest trying their chole bhature on weekends, but go early to avoid missing out!😌","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4HJxReyJesVaJYG9Yx_z3NfhusxRqp3rBwuIa&fid=0x0:0x989223df5dbaf36a"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Simranjit Singh Bhatia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhsN8E9VLHyguWqMd_rKUWH9hk3Z8_kCUBPnccUYiIo-6XzJAJ9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently dined at this new restaurant in Mission, and it was a fantastic experience. The food is fresh, delicious, and made to order with top-notch ingredients. The owners are friendly, and the prices are reasonable. The Chole Bhature were definitely a standout, and we cannot wait to return for more. This place is a must-visit if you're craving authentic Delhi flavoured food or just a delightful meal!
Now, based on our own experience, we ordered a variety of other dishes including fish pakora, veg momos, chicken lababdar, and goat curry. We also tried their Mango Burfi and everything was simply delicious.
As everything is made to order, giving the owners a heads-up of your arrival is recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmgKDZDuiWn6krzpfjlbvjqQuU8D167wWoIzA6&fid=0x0:0x989223df5dbaf36a"],"When":"2023-11-4"},{"Name":"Abhinandan Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1cyRwNoAPFOpP-jO31yivGXsb7UlVYtJeMT_Ne6ROORT-7jE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Truly India offers a flavorful and authentic dining experience, with a wide variety of traditional Indian dishes. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, and the service is friendly and attentive. A great choice for anyone craving quality Indian cuisine.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Jui-Ting Hsu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzMTH8WdaJedBJ0cRjGUnxM_bF0Rh-hfad2E-0vfW11MjCCi70=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Currently nestled within the same area as Locality Brewing, Stampede Burger is a very innocuous looking food truck, removed from the hustle and bustle of major traffic. Especially in the winter hours when the sun sets at an earlier time, the atmosphere can come off as a little foreboding - but if you give the staff of both Stampede Burger and Locality Brewing a visit, they'll handsomely reward you with some of the most delectable (and gamey) food and drink available.

Stampede Burger mostly specializes in bison, with poutine and burger offered in ample portions, though they also do offer black bean burgers for the vegetarian-inclined. (I did not inquire on whether they could make this vegan-based, but it may be possible.)
Seating is also plentiful in the area,, with a fire-lit patio if you choose to peruse Locality Brewing's offerings nearby. The entrance and exit are dimly lit, however, so caution to those who drive in the later hours (e.g. Fridays at night).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Isabela Laurin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAKRB6-5oqF6sgpqjKo3Y4vNI9iuK7j2iswtJRLRgkcaS7Bpxtmg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My new favourite burger place! Absolutely delicious and there is lots of seating. The service was excellent, everyone was wonderful. 😁","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trevor Vaughan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWL6Gf2IY_2PYeaJBNt4Z1q5Jz2ftwRxVHjvJ79wwoC3pbXdkk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super underrated food truck! Excellent staff and even better burgers, I highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Neil Vaughan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQRcddGpwnhZFiizpo4Oka0h7PxGxHtsA_gX3WRlD-PgaSbKq5=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent burger and great location!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Carrie-Anne Vaughan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKZZIhZQONOWOPQzmlxG1TOeW5rK6tuUOm8NlnYyZwhsZ2wjA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"WILLIAM REN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKRmqUVmhhErGGqKi-Bzn0et1-EnBX9lgvZO2NQ0f1pzZpZEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Browns Socialhouse is Vancouver-based franchise restaurant. It features West Coast-inspired dishes and some Asian Flavours. The atmosphere is cozy with light music. Many friends would like enjoy the Brunch served on weekends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOqnY04ENUI-fXHfTsQCqlkGofgnolOPNz2U5Wb\u0026fid=0x0:0x6cc32a05f8c5866d"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Blue Jay ProWash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKwsMpxf0zD_UDIwqm8AWv-dSjMAuw_b7CfLk3O6FQeBWWmw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had fantastic lunch with our family! Thank you, staff are great, and food is fabulous! Our 4 year old was happy too and it with healthy chicken and rice option!:) :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhWXqCGrwQ9CSeue8lzM14Qgwpdx2BC6YuNXBt\u0026fid=0x0:0x6cc32a05f8c5866d"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Paxton Skrukwa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLIn2o1TGm6qhK760ufU-Ks7kFr_uE1jgLQEnBiAZxtwNR7zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I need to watch my sugar intake ,  asked about a drink if it had sugar was told no, asked the manager and she says yes it has simple syrup but it's not in the ingredients list in the menu which I found troubling . They took the drink back but the dragon bowl I ordered must have had 20x the sugar that the drink had. The bowl itself tasted entirely of sweet sugary sauce.i could have achieved this same flavour with rice, sauce and chicken  at home . Got the bill and was still charged for the drink so I asked and got it fixed. I should have just said I had a intolerance to sugar at the beginning and the meal would have been made to fit my needs and I regret that . Restaurants should be putting the food information on the menu, grams of sugar / calories etc. as lots of people are health conscious nowadays . Id recommend the spicy chicken burger  and that's probably all I'm going to order from now on .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thomas Schoen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4HuE2qC3eytZFujoTyLbI7P9baqhbwAZw2INFz3f0MnUU_jlk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had a really great experience at the Mission location of Brown's Social House. Service was friendly and timely, given the dinner rush hour timing. We started with a share plate of Nachos for our table of 3 and it was just the right amount and delicious. The branded, in-house IPA was quite good and I re-ordered. For my main dish I went for the Steak Frites and the steak was a nice cut and cooked well. Fries were not very crispy and a little on the cold site, hence only 4 stars for the meal. However, tis is a great location and I will be coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAlKO_ODAqpVeRYETi4uFz8c0nOUlAnVYV_PN1\u0026fid=0x0:0x6cc32a05f8c5866d"],"When":"2024-5-10"},{"Name":"Christine Pearl Agustin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzXynYpxJLtauuPFz4BuyDmBv2mPUL3JYNi0AHus83F0CzFSzw4w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"brown’s socialhouse is a nice and modern restaurant with a cozy indoor atmosphere. i ordered the alfredo pasta with chicken breast and garlic bread on the side. while the chicken breast was flavorful and juicy, the pasta sauce had a slight taste that didn’t sit well with me, so it wasn’t the best. aside from that, the portions were good, and the service was excellent!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFnlZCgiNVzjVq3EYzlnsm2f7q-q5iSjqbzZ5M\u0026fid=0x0:0x6cc32a05f8c5866d"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"James Mendonca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDOYVs1G-8iT9QF6Fj3_nUauDo1DS6zISrEp3lZ9wij4inDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This Browns Socialhouse is a great place for brunch and dinner. The coffee was good, not the best. However, I really enjoyed their Berries \u0026 Cream French toast; it was crunchy, moist, warm and all-around delicious. The Service was courteous to your needs, making sure you are not neglected as a customer. And I always liked their indoor decor with the portraits. I will be coming back there soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNnKJyB3cyD4FzJjxbWCVHu0P5u5MnOJ8TwFoj_\u0026fid=0x0:0x6cc32a05f8c5866d"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"Nicole Martin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVH1KSADJZTVqeKjOjrpbcXLg9nTOeHiijEFuEWVHRF1P6qkoM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The tomato baguette sandwich was amazing.  We added the grilled chicken which was so tender.  The soup was hot and delicious as the coffee.   Shared this luncheon with my aunt and it takes a lot to impress her.  She was!  Only thing if someone has hearing aids the music is a little too loud.  But otherwise a nice place!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Benedicto Rodríguez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVcidtirjtHUboty39C9BKOXu1J4XYuc_SWLh_YQTggDovM1fsbjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything is okay. It's a good place for lunch and a good time! The waiter was great!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMo-p43yGzwt1ZY30qnRNqjbbB5HPk0q4k8P_V0\u0026fid=0x0:0x6cc32a05f8c5866d"],"When":"2024-7-12"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Devin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKH0n5aZzXMRAQ3XA1Fji0egGBAN_NyQwluMXduDViiNm5vBw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mission City Pizza has become my go-to spot! The pizza is always top-notch, with super fresh veggies that taste like they were picked that day. The quality really shows in every bite. And the prices? Unbeatable for the amount of flavor and quality you get. But what really surprised me was their drink section—I’ve never seen such a huge selection in Canada!

Highly recommend this place if you’re looking for amazing pizza and an awesome value!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhzSgxoselnhaAP4uepgoKTLwvfw_019T1IvUE&fid=0x0:0xae87277a9b87a394"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Don Adlam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRt53_YsjgMS2F7nWoaXYxJIpS4pPiJCdxAhCNqKceRU2Y2dqqOg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! We were at Camp Luther and they had some mission city pizzas. They were loaded. We got in the truck and came straight here and the guy is so friendly. Also the store is clean and has cool artwork.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1xxr_r0z0TLwTbaGEbIOxxR2eOJ5lYdTx8Kkk&fid=0x0:0xae87277a9b87a394"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Rajkaran Sidhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKpLFAD9JStWvDJiaPziwd6yJ0EL8W1ZbFHvrfw3J7uX9R2Vw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently tried Mission City Pizza, and wow, I was blown away. Best pizza ever!

The sauce and crust really stood out to me—it has that perfect balance between crispy and soft, with a flavourful sauce and it complements the pizza without overpowering it. But the cheese… I can’t get over how perfectly melted it is. They don’t skimp on it either, which I love. Every bite was packed with flavor. If you’re looking for a local pizza spot that nails it every time, Mission City Pizza is a must-try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2LQIFJlItoLigkkQcNehGql_HP4mtX11Frr2i&fid=0x0:0xae87277a9b87a394"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Anmol Grover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKkR45pEkn9SB_PgiLAyFXkhbzWLnq8A4chve3r8qfmJbRwZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you haven’t tried Mission City Pizza yet, you are seriously missing out on the best pizza!

Perfectly crispy crust, loaded with fresh, flavourful toppings, and cheese that melts in your mouth. It’s my new go to pizza place and I’m truly hooked on the Tropical Hawaiian. 🤤❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwyy1XgZgfH8fwLq-CGRXmaZa-jWnFcmCyU2Aa&fid=0x0:0xae87277a9b87a394"],"When":"2024-9-11"},{"Name":"Sophie Saran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLmgs5EhzYg95E7LlnYwt_gNGtk0b6V4F_3_iN3kowRObaFeQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mission Pizza is hands down the best pizza out there! The flavors are just incredible, and they’re generous with the fresh veggies and top-quality ingredients. Every bite tastes so fresh, you can really tell they use the best of the best. I’ve tried a lot of pizza in Surrey, and nothing even comes close to how good this is – it slaps every single time! My favorite is the veggie pizza, and it hits the spot every time. My mouth’s watering just thinking about it! Seriously, I wish they had a location in Surrey so I could grab it more often. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hassan Mk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUn8XljJKUWtM5hZCcrws3Ntw3dFgRbwi5l6-83UHe5aX-z7xYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"On a sunny day, my family and I visited here, hoping for a delightful experience. We opted for the Greek Special Pizza, but unfortunately, it fell short of expectations. While the base was commendable, the overwhelming amount of onions dominated the flavor, leaving little room for other ingredients to shine. Adding some dried minced beef even made it worse.

Moreover, the lack of air conditioning in the shop made the wait for our order unbearable, especially on a hot day. Despite this discomfort, the staff remained courteous and accommodating throughout our visit, which was a saving grace.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3TW_g37MD6vstP_eEp_VtvxDpvCZrSjiizSS6&fid=0x0:0xae87277a9b87a394"],"When":"2024-5-12"},{"Name":"Danielle Windecker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWok-HuPXFDirjF2qkQTD0QDJW82jUHorG1OT_CuQi8xiEQRIqEtw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We love Mission City Pizza! We're new to Mission and weren't certain if we'd get delivery where we are but these folks happily obliged. On top of that they were 20 minutes faster than expected. Pizzas were piping hot and fresh. We appreciate the tasty crusts and finely chopped toppings. Delivery person was also smiley and patient. Will absolutely order again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"James Mendonca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDOYVs1G-8iT9QF6Fj3_nUauDo1DS6zISrEp3lZ9wij4inDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My father used to order from Mission City Pizza a lot, even though he tends to order from every new in town pizza place. I still enjoy their pizzas. I ordered the usual pepperoni pizza, large. The overall pizza was really good. The cheese is gooey, as it should be, the crust is fresh and crunchy with doughy thickness, the pepperoni topping is reasonable, yet still has porky, salty taste to it. The pizza was scarce with its sauce. My only other complaint was the parking at Mission City is very minimum and it was located on the corner where the convenience store used to be. And I am someone who prefers pick-up over delivery. I enjoyed their pizza and I might order from them again soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWbLqlTpifvbE9KTOjuMriwyT4HYYbc_jUT7l7&fid=0x0:0xae87277a9b87a394"],"When":"2024-12-18"}]

[{"Name":"Harley Pan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8Qq433-Ar1XcNkStIszjJ1vPqO_xcJopX5NLhTAwlv5u-LvY-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a tourist, I regret so much going to SABA cafe across the street. Blacksmith Bakery is so much better. The croissants are bigger than my face. It’s crispy and full of layers. The pastry looks professionally made and taste delicious. Most importantly, their hot food options are really good too. Good sandwiches, good soup.

Come here instead of SABA.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqupHgaugSUednF-t5qfrTmF2UDZroPz7eqCSf&fid=0x0:0x3b15df3e07bb54f3"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"joanna ch","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXibOrMfRatQRTgVyt2rNvdN0IjcJMpMZ0slAO-N-RK6HAlw9KB=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered Truly Chocolate Cake & Lemon Meringue Tart on my recent visit.  I love them both.
Was gonna try the croissants, but unfortunately saw flies in the open shelf.
Latte was good, too.  Bought a pack of coffee beans before leaving.  :)
If the bakery is much closer to my home, I will definitely come visiting often.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKrvJYlmsaSP8MnF9CqGcjsFaEsfuL1sqDilQ5&fid=0x0:0x3b15df3e07bb54f3"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Kim Lishman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoLip5cDVmyG9tqCTLI4iijakhf4W2VYZg3aEWyBWtOfnKc61HDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The most amazing salted maple latte I've ever had! Such a great flavour combination and the coffee was smooth and creamy. We also tried the bread and butter pudding croissant which was delicious. Came on a Sunday afternoon and the line was out the door but worth it for the latte. Lots of seating outside and inside.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXAm4w0zXhSj8NCnf8nUZnaHGU3fgAaCTZbhyz&fid=0x0:0x3b15df3e07bb54f3"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Danilo Teodoro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_rV4_xok36vIezJ6uAhpzSfyECA8ogmjA4ehyXVTr4dBqIAFv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The Pain au Chocolat was crispy and tasty! user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Gen X Surrey Girl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnz98iwXPE1DskfLpfNg-zDV5mDy1tGmvmbNcHWdRqf6q4OTmNvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Thanks for the choking hazard. See below.

Not too happy with this location for many reasons. To start, I placed an online order for mac and  cheese and it said 45 mins. Seriously? Okay, so I guess I'll have to wait. After 15 mins I went in, the place was empty and my food was sitting on the counter. If there is no wait why does the app say 45 mins? My food would've just sat there getting cold for another 30 mins.

My level 3 spice was non-existant. It says level one has a mild dose of heat. Level two is for hot lovers only. I ordered number three and tasted no spice whatsoever.

There were no onions and no red peppers in the order as advertised. I didn't see or taste any cilantro that was supposed to be included according to the menu. And I wasn't a fan of the whole cherry tomatoes tossed in instead of the diced tomatoes shown in the photo.

It's an extra $5 for meat which is ridiculous considering it's already almost 20 bucks for mac and cheese and the quantity of meat they add is tiny. The char siu add-on was disgusting and gnarly. It was like chewing gum.

The food didn't taste nearly as good as other noodle box locations. Hardly any sauce and really lacking in flavor.

Another thing that really bothered me is when I went to pull off the plastic lid it was so brittle it cracked into pieces that fell into my food leaving clear sharp jagged plastic bits in my food. How poor is the quality of their supplies that you can't even pull off a lid without it crumbling into pieces? I wasn't rough with it. And it happened the first time it was pulled off. It must've been really old or exposed to heat or sunlight to be so fragile.

As for the atmosphere, I thought this place was fairly new. Why does it feel like a dank, dirty pub from the 80s?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPjRH-HHPbJ3zfhRfPdIjpfTovlYcy20y66uij&fid=0x0:0x91ad6a7f3bd089a4"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Brandon Stewart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLkm3BRUVR43kzVWblXsgFPHcgenlpMHz_VwRsy957NDVfdYw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If I could give zero stars I would.
Disgusting place.
This restaurant has screwed me around multiple times.
This time they served me moldy noodles, every noodle in my bowl was littered in mold, and when I brought the food back to show them all gave me was a free order and 15% off..
The shift manager was no help as she tried to deny these allegations even though the mold was right infront of her face.
I’d like the owner to contact me or food safe will be getting involved.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPxXJ07_DJLj_l8o9ntZkhN6L_RQ2UEie-YVxN&fid=0x0:0x91ad6a7f3bd089a4"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Xanaphia Xangel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_seHMrjSrnxKKFO83cfvdunybCw5ja6M_3nSpcSL1-33Wfq-r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Staff is great, they make suggestions, they listen to your order attentively. It you are not sure they have made some great suggestions that have always resulted in those who I introduce to the restaurant happy and full.
My personal favourite is the spicy peanut noodle box (pic below)
I find their prices to be fair (on average two noodle boxes +tip $40 or less)
They have a few save choices for kids including mac n cheese (I haven't tried it but I'm curious) and a chow mein.
The seating area is pretty bland, that's the only reason I give it 4* not 5*.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNrqkoY-9jAnFtWa5Ii5uxdbW_Sa4CyW-E38fy&fid=0x0:0x91ad6a7f3bd089a4"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Alexis Boorman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXfu07sdzCW-EWLVOR24VJfMQS_SXSjQQRZDIj0S0HcD4LutLywZw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I was so excited to get noodlebox tonight, I used to get it on the Island in Nanaimo fairly often. Decided to try the Thai style chow mein with crispy tofu… unfortunately it has almost zero flavour, very slight hint of curry. The noodles are super dry, the veggies seem like they’ve been sitting around all day. The tofu is the opposite of crispy, it’s dry, soggy, chewy. We live 5 min max away and it wasn’t sitting long enough to turn into this. I know, because my bf’s dish was fine, everything in his bowl seemed fresh. I was looking forward to not leaving the house this Sunday but with the cost of food, I can’t justify not going back and getting my moneys worth of something possibly more edible than this. It looks a lot better than it tastes..

*Editing and adding a couple stars, I brought the food back and they remade my bowl with a different option at no charge, which I greatly appreciate. However, they mentioned they would never recommend the chow mein dish as they agree it’s flavourless and not very good. They also said there was an issue with the deep fryer. My suggestion to avoid future disappointed customers would be to ask if they’ve had it before.. and suggest a different option if they’ve never had it. Secondly, if the deep fryer isn’t working, it would be better to advise the customer to choose a different protein or suggest plain tofu instead of crispy. You can’t help if there’s crappy dishes on the menu and it’s a chain so you may not be able to remove it, but there’s ways around it by offering different options to avoid disappointment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMU-DAWYGACiZHsE_xdjg630rLFkHxZHLXaIcp1&fid=0x0:0x91ad6a7f3bd089a4"],"When":"2024-1-22"},{"Name":"Cody C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuV9gG_hr6FBp8SeUw9lQQ2-zPDVWRtVgiikbv3uRsyAA7dmim=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst Noodlebox around. Screwed up our DoorDash order both times. Every time I've gone in to do take out it's been dead with no one in there and they say minimum 30/40 minute wait. I've never waited that long at ANY other Noodlebox. I'll go to Abbotsford or PoCo before I'll ever come back here. Was so excited to have a Noodlebox in Mission but these guys ruined it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"brian smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpS3kkF8tOiRevIsbwfmuWkrV2GWBglrexweF2_JA2gYyRnLs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered dinner for three adults and 2 children. I ordered the butter chicken it was very greasy oily and did not taste fresh.
My Daughter ordered noodle/crispy
Chicken/ vegetable and I have been holding her hair while she threw up for the last hour.
My daughter never gets sick and 100% was what she ate. I looked at her leftovers and the noodles seem to be soggy and the veggies don’t look fresh.
As a first time customer I regret stopping at this location.
The food did not look fresh and has either
Been over prepped or sitting to long.
For some context I have cooked professionally for 15 years.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lexi Janos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXEHnFR0KCp9ZhhVsp0paJoGehX_kyQjVCumFEymRO7tyfnQ1CKDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I ordered a Thai style chow mein with rice noodles, fried egg, and Thai basil. Upon opening, the Thai basil was just left on top and in the time it took for door dash to deliver it had turned brown and the whole meal smelled like rotten basil. I took it off and everything was still piping hot so I was excited to dig in. Unfortunately, the excitement quickly left. I got medium spice, and while there was decent spice, it had no flavour. It was a mushy, bland, pile of spice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMib2Wk_vsBV0bFFgcqCatReIr3fJo6FwFGz076&fid=0x0:0x91ad6a7f3bd089a4"],"When":"2023-7-17"},{"Name":"Kim Larson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWu7RKt-8vHtBvT7wSMXsQ-YP1HgGUtSv1bdip0Jvg4iMzTF3Se=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ordered multiple dishes (family of 5) and all were not great. The rice was hard. The pork extra chewy. The Naan was dry. Inconsistent spice, as we ordered a mild spice and we've had this dish before and tonight my teen daughter couldn't finish her meal as it was too hot.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Danial in the kitchen turns out some amazing grub. Today I had the tortilla soup and added shredded beef. I think it might be one of the best things I’ve ever ate. 10/10 recommend making this your go to spot too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLcNZuZVMQiH0kaV8v_fqKyDvpl-wRNglkL8Jo&fid=0x0:0xbdb00602ef84b335"],"When":"2024-4-26"},{"Name":"Garret Visser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhZea4eg8L2G4Nm4-IL9DlT1s23HLahA4DHFKlmMZS5bO_IQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was amazing, server was new but very friendly and learning fast. Prices were great.

The one thing that stood out, and I personally do not care, but others might: (warning bit of a story)

I asked for the bill because I was not aware you had to go up to pay at the front which is fine, the new server brought me the bill on a tray that said “thank you” and someone had been using the tray to roll joints on it before LOL(see weed crumbs on the tray in picture) Not a big deal for me at all, the food made up for it, but maybe make sure those trays don’t get mixed up with the bill trays 😂.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMVvbAqoZ4D5DSI1M-RxCUi6uUrkkKktrL__Le&fid=0x0:0xbdb00602ef84b335"],"When":"2024-8-10"},{"Name":"TZ Moving","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLFWjWUJULWNQ3Z2ac-zBgVNiXLSOO1LjFv86WXKQWvTyESJA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food, staff, and the restaurant it’s self is AMAZING… took my daughter here for lunch the waiter so very friendly the food was perfect and authentic and it was very kid friendly lots to look at and talk about !! Will recommend to all friends and family. Thanks for having us 🙌🏼","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdo9o6FTN_7DiG1qaEx8jcfbjh3Zb3hYFFYFNM&fid=0x0:0xbdb00602ef84b335"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"James Mendonca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDOYVs1G-8iT9QF6Fj3_nUauDo1DS6zISrEp3lZ9wij4inDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have been to Corona's Mexican restaurant and have had decent experiences. This time not so much. There was available seating right away and I was treated with water without ice, as ordered. I had the Chimichanga with shredded pork. The side dishes were solid decent and I had one chimichanga with green spicy sauce and the other had red mild sauce. The green was very spicy and made me sweat a lot while the red one was better and was able to better taste the overall chimichanga. The service was subpar to say the least. When I received my entree, I was given a spoon instead of a fork and it took sometime for the waiter to refill my water while eating the spicy chimichangas. I like the cultural design of the establishment. Visiting Corona's was not the worst experience, yet it is not the best either. I hope that next time I come I will have a better time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgE0lGdGpqvXVvVfcsEcnXBLTqma_kdei6G9Wa&fid=0x0:0xbdb00602ef84b335"],"When":"2023-11-6"},{"Name":"Jordan Rempel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-oAJ8p-5_NMmepQWskrMyhIJYRN8ccdGsJCukeo0GAHtmHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been here a couple times, but there has been such a big improvement since I’ve been here! Friendly and accommodating staff, (and a wonderful authentic atmosphere. I hope they never take the asada fries off the menu. They were delicious! Will definitely be back! Great place to end a movie night :)","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"J W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJo-Cmrc1HZduOPETsbTPLkBkL6YnB-OGT_-IXnca5j7zZRJA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Been renamed! Changed menu and maybe new management.

No longer has the fish burger but we got the cheeseburger and it was pretty good. My kids gobbled it up. I think it was because of the thousand island sauce, similar to the Big Mac. The big news is actually that they serve Starbucks coffee and beverages now!! Haven’t tried it yet but I suspect this is a huge upgrade from before and will definitely be stopping by for a coffee/beverage at the start of our visit so I can just stroll, sip and enjoy.

Also final note that I think the trimmed down/focused menu is a good move. Do a few things well rather than trying to do a lot of options with subpar results. Also no more microwave.

—
Concession was surprisingly decent with options. Fish burger was good. Strips were alright. There’s plenty of seating. High chairs for babies. A microwave even! Washrooms were clean. I would recommend making your lunch stop here. Only wish there were healthy options for kids — I suggest you bring your own food for young kids.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMIkj_gFn199kHOCSK4boFzxw3mTuvnHAvlS-uf&fid=0x0:0x2929b1f51257e599"],"When":"2022-9-11"},{"Name":"FanShu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWmCCNWhQTwnhquddpyVMJ9b-ZtdWkwlYZK_d701v1bu9bGGOVl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Their cheeseburger is surprisingly good with fresh ingredients in it. Their popcorn chicken, not so much...

Definitely would NOT recommend the popcorn chicken. It was mainly chicken skin and was nowhere near the quality and quantity in the menu picture. The chicken was way overcooked and were extremely small. The meat was about 1 cm by 1 cm. Please see attached photo. FYI, it didn't come with the fries in case you were wondering. Kentucky fried chicken's popcorn chicken is way better.

I tried to eat it all since it was $8 but it was just too hard to chew...

Staff were nice!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlwx4Hb4jGZhF7Q9UunfLFydW0Rv8HH5wYxq68&fid=0x0:0x2929b1f51257e599"],"When":"2022-10-15"},{"Name":"Hannah Ruller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHhxJJpRHtEYJW_ZI5Y6rlkEnAXueiHAGLY_eVWkULiEit3lU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I thought there was a good selection of food available, lots of variety. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"James Mendonca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDOYVs1G-8iT9QF6Fj3_nUauDo1DS6zISrEp3lZ9wij4inDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Eleni’s is a great Greek restaurant. The establishment is sophisticated and has low lighting, something I like in any restaurant. The workers are professional and courteous. The food is magnificent and comes in great portions. I would recommend the Kalamari Caesar Salad, the Hunter Schnitzel and the Oscar-style Steak. My only issue with this restaurant is that they are no longer open for lunch. Besides that, I highly recommend anyone who loves Greek food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrw0qollxVx68RqD-me7YPMqsYrQj-bq_wP1wf&fid=0x0:0x506fdee1a6ecf5f3"],"When":"2023-10-9"},{"Name":"Christian Metatron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWbB71b_6BYyu3cZ6xoveog7lX2YqgJi2mdnK2HUb7ekKzx5V6I1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food, our server was friendly, informative and professional. It was my sister and niece's birthday and the staff brought out a delicious Greek dessert. It was a pudding made from a secret recipe. It was delicious. We will definitely be going back. I highly recommend this restaurant 💫💫💫💫💫","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjiySIjQeNbui8JbwtpkrGw3Xea6aO9yvktUQ-&fid=0x0:0x506fdee1a6ecf5f3"],"When":"2023-12-12"},{"Name":"Paul Roberts","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQqzxaZ9-XVD1EznpAc46Szk3Pzf-KS9Mpekqwj6YwaelpCwh95g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We arrived at about 5:30 pm on a Saturday. Lots of street parking out front. Was busy-ish, no reservation, seated promptly. Server was courteous and consistently popped by to see to our needs. The restaurant hasn’t changed much over the years but still looks good and is a comfortable place to eat.
We ordered the seafood linguini with a Greek salad to start. The salad was fresh, crunchy and so delicious, as well as a really good portion.
The linguini came with two pieces of fresh but crispy garlic toast and a mountain of shrimp, prawn and scallops. Lovely creamy sauce and the pasta was just right.
Neither one of us finished it as it was a large portion, so leftovers for lunch tomorrow, yum.
The only thing I will say, is the prices seem to have really crept up. While I didn’t feel taken advantage of, I didn’t feel like “what a great deal”. Having said that, we did take both entree leftovers home.
It’s delicious food, it’s good service and a decent value.
The Greek side of the menu is small, and they do serve everything from burgers to bbq. They have a kids and seniors section too.
A great family restaurant that still won’t break the bank.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtTqmt3o-ILgE4DqSNxbPCOAu5jgRKEGqHJDui&fid=0x0:0x506fdee1a6ecf5f3"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Tom Baker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMvMP9y5qsJWw7LpWZbOYuqZ2tYp6FAN6VrvqAa4AbftejqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Somewhat dated interior, but the food is good. The portion sizes are decent too. This place is a staple for Greek food for me. And I drive in about 45 minutes to eat here.

I highly recommend the Greek platter for 2. It’s a great assortment of food. The calamari is very perfectly done.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Heidi Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKmM-7hhdDD2gmotK-bwNaiqVqtZvWvq2td0CC_HMFQR-AIJ1X=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of my go to places to eat In Mission. There was 4 of us. We ordered the Captains platter, seafood fettuccine, pita bread/tzatziki sauce, chicken burger and chicken schnitzels. They are known for their very garlic taste in their Caesar salads but for the last couple of visits it hadn’t been the same. I was told a different person makes them. Please please keep the strong garlic taste, it’s why I come there!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOr02j9uJEB9Ne3HwBYSvFtk9h6sRD0zeqHsnkd&fid=0x0:0x506fdee1a6ecf5f3"],"When":"2023-3-8"},{"Name":"Jane Dizon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIs-Vq1Ou_49gnryHb9JXiSNOjxPLKNCmlIUjJiPc9e6Jy6ccKT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Greek food craving satisfied in Downtown Mission!  Great value for your money.
The platters are a wonderful way to try the dishes and different flavors.
Friendly and attentive staff.  How we wish businesses like Eleni's will continue to thrive in Mission.  Support local!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxuYIf9zAuUPUPAB1hgIjTHARxz88wJ0OEw58Q&fid=0x0:0x506fdee1a6ecf5f3"],"When":"2022-1-8"},{"Name":"Sarah Droz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL8WFvfE6tmyP200DTQhQDMLe2-M90uF0ONGP3VjnQCniJVHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered for pick up, but when I picked up the price was 30% more than prices listed on the website. Our 2 lamb dinners came to 20$ more than listed. When I brought this to their attention I was told they couldn't change the website. Eventually they gave me 2 pieces of custard, but wouldn't give the food at the listed price or even a discount. When I suggested they warn people that call to order that the prices aren't as listed,  or give them a total over the phone I was told they have to add it up with a calculator and got a shrug and a sorry. I feel bad for the server at the til.
The food is alright, but when you're expecting to pay 50$ for take out and are charged $70 it really takes away from the experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Krista Hole","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEXo3-V2CjTOG6XSOVVMNxDnqpckLkrnmAdZ_E77liLbluTz-d=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was fantastic, service was wonderful. All around a great night especially for my kiddo, they interacted with him which was great.","Images":null,"When":""}]
